4600
4601/*[clinic input]
4602os.utime
4603
4604 path: path_t(allow_fd='PATH_UTIME_HAVE_FD')
4605 times: object = NULL
4606 *
4607 ns: object = NULL
4608 dir_fd: dir_fd(requires='futimensat') = None
4609 follow_symlinks: bool=True
4610
4611# "utime(path, times=None, *[, ns], dir_fd=None, follow_symlinks=True)\n\
4612
4613Set the access and modified time of path.
4614
4615path may always be specified as a string.
4616On some platforms, path may also be specified as an open file descriptor.
4617 If this functionality is unavailable, using it raises an exception.
4618
4619If times is not None, it must be a tuple (atime, mtime);
4620 atime and mtime should be expressed as float seconds since the epoch.
4621If ns is specified, it must be a tuple (atime_ns, mtime_ns);
4622 atime_ns and mtime_ns should be expressed as integer nanoseconds
4623 since the epoch.
4624If times is None and ns is unspecified, utime uses the current time.
4625Specifying tuples for both times and ns is an error.
4626
4627If dir_fd is not None, it should be a file descriptor open to a directory,
4628 and path should be relative; path will then be relative to that directory.
4629If follow_symlinks is False, and the last element of the path is a symbolic
4630 link, utime will modify the symbolic link itself instead of the file the
4631 link points to.
4632It is an error to use dir_fd or follow_symlinks when specifying path
4633 as an open file descriptor.
4634dir_fd and follow_symlinks may not be available on your platform.
4635 If they are unavailable, using them will raise a NotImplementedError.
4636
4637[clinic start generated code]*/
4638
4639static PyObject *
4640os_utime_impl(PyObject *module, path_t *path, PyObject *times, PyObject *ns,
4641 int dir_fd, int follow_symlinks)
4642/*[clinic end generated code: output=cfcac69d027b82cf input=081cdc54ca685385]*/
4643{
4644#ifdef MS_WINDOWS
4645 HANDLE hFile;
4646 FILETIME atime, mtime;
4647#else
4648 int result;
4649#endif
4650
4651 PyObject *return_value = NULL;
4652 utime_t utime;
4653
4654 memset(&utime, 0, sizeof(utime_t));
4655
4656 if (times && (times != Py_None) && ns) {
4657 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError,
4658 "utime: you may specify either 'times'"
4659 " or 'ns' but not both");
4660 goto exit;
4661 }
4662
4663 if (times && (times != Py_None)) {
4664 time_t a_sec, m_sec;
4665 long a_nsec, m_nsec;
4666 if (!PyTuple_CheckExact(times) || (PyTuple_Size(times) != 2)) {
4667 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
4668 "utime: 'times' must be either"
4669 " a tuple of two ints or None");
4670 goto exit;
4671 }
4672 utime.now = 0;
4673 if (_PyTime_ObjectToTimespec(PyTuple_GET_ITEM(times, 0),
4674 &a_sec, &a_nsec, _PyTime_ROUND_FLOOR) == -1 ||
4675 _PyTime_ObjectToTimespec(PyTuple_GET_ITEM(times, 1),
4676 &m_sec, &m_nsec, _PyTime_ROUND_FLOOR) == -1) {
4677 goto exit;
4678 }
4679 utime.atime_s = a_sec;
4680 utime.atime_ns = a_nsec;
4681 utime.mtime_s = m_sec;
4682 utime.mtime_ns = m_nsec;
4683 }
4684 else if (ns) {
4685 if (!PyTuple_CheckExact(ns) || (PyTuple_Size(ns) != 2)) {
4686 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
4687 "utime: 'ns' must be a tuple of two ints");
4688 goto exit;
4689 }
4690 utime.now = 0;
4691 if (!split_py_long_to_s_and_ns(PyTuple_GET_ITEM(ns, 0),
4692 &utime.atime_s, &utime.atime_ns) ||
4693 !split_py_long_to_s_and_ns(PyTuple_GET_ITEM(ns, 1),
4694 &utime.mtime_s, &utime.mtime_ns)) {
4695 goto exit;
4696 }
4697 }
4698 else {
4699 /* times and ns are both None/unspecified. use "now". */
4700 utime.now = 1;
4701 }
4702
4703#if !defined(UTIME_HAVE_NOFOLLOW_SYMLINKS)
4704 if (follow_symlinks_specified("utime", follow_symlinks))
4705 goto exit;
4706#endif
4707
4708 if (path_and_dir_fd_invalid("utime", path, dir_fd) ||
4709 dir_fd_and_fd_invalid("utime", dir_fd, path->fd) ||
4710 fd_and_follow_symlinks_invalid("utime", path->fd, follow_symlinks))
4711 goto exit;
4712
4713#if !defined(HAVE_UTIMENSAT)
4714 if ((dir_fd != DEFAULT_DIR_FD) && (!follow_symlinks)) {
4715 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError,
4716 "utime: cannot use dir_fd and follow_symlinks "
4717 "together on this platform");
4718 goto exit;
4719 }
4720#endif
4721
4722#ifdef MS_WINDOWS
4723 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
4724 hFile = CreateFileW(path->wide, FILE_WRITE_ATTRIBUTES, 0,
4725 NULL, OPEN_EXISTING,
4726 FILE_FLAG_BACKUP_SEMANTICS, NULL);
4727 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
4728 if (hFile == INVALID_HANDLE_VALUE) {
4729 path_error(path);
4730 goto exit;
4731 }
4732
4733 if (utime.now) {
4734 GetSystemTimeAsFileTime(&mtime);
4735 atime = mtime;
4736 }
4737 else {
4738 _Py_time_t_to_FILE_TIME(utime.atime_s, utime.atime_ns, &atime);
4739 _Py_time_t_to_FILE_TIME(utime.mtime_s, utime.mtime_ns, &mtime);
4740 }
4741 if (!SetFileTime(hFile, NULL, &atime, &mtime)) {
4742 /* Avoid putting the file name into the error here,
4743 as that may confuse the user into believing that
4744 something is wrong with the file, when it also
4745 could be the time stamp that gives a problem. */
4746 PyErr_SetFromWindowsErr(0);
4747 goto exit;
4748 }
4749#else /* MS_WINDOWS */
4750 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
4751
4752#ifdef UTIME_HAVE_NOFOLLOW_SYMLINKS
4753 if ((!follow_symlinks) && (dir_fd == DEFAULT_DIR_FD))
4754 result = utime_nofollow_symlinks(&utime, path->narrow);
4755 else
4756#endif
4757
4758#if defined(HAVE_FUTIMESAT) || defined(HAVE_UTIMENSAT)
4759 if ((dir_fd != DEFAULT_DIR_FD) || (!follow_symlinks))
4760 result = utime_dir_fd(&utime, dir_fd, path->narrow, follow_symlinks);
4761 else
4762#endif
4763
4764#if defined(HAVE_FUTIMES) || defined(HAVE_FUTIMENS)
4765 if (path->fd != -1)
4766 result = utime_fd(&utime, path->fd);
4767 else
4768#endif
4769
4770 result = utime_default(&utime, path->narrow);
4771
4772 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
4773
4774 if (result < 0) {
4775 /* see previous comment about not putting filename in error here */
4776 return_value = posix_error();
4777 goto exit;
4778 }
4779
4780#endif /* MS_WINDOWS */
4781
4782 Py_INCREF(Py_None);
4783 return_value = Py_None;
4784
4785exit:
4786#ifdef MS_WINDOWS
4787 if (hFile != INVALID_HANDLE_VALUE)
4788 CloseHandle(hFile);
4789#endif
4790 return return_value;
4791}

4812#if defined(HAVE_WEXECV) || defined(HAVE_WSPAWNV)
4813#define EXECV_CHAR wchar_t
4814#else
4815#define EXECV_CHAR char
4816#endif
4817
4818#if defined(HAVE_EXECV) || defined(HAVE_SPAWNV)
4819static void
4820free_string_array(EXECV_CHAR **array, Py_ssize_t count)
4821{
4822 Py_ssize_t i;
4823 for (i = 0; i < count; i++)
4824 PyMem_Free(array[i]);
4825 PyMem_DEL(array);
4826}
4827
4828static int
4829fsconvert_strdup(PyObject *o, EXECV_CHAR **out)
4830{
4831 Py_ssize_t size;
4832 PyObject *ub;
4833 int result = 0;
4834#if defined(HAVE_WEXECV) || defined(HAVE_WSPAWNV)
4835 if (!PyUnicode_FSDecoder(o, &ub))
4836 return 0;
4837 *out = PyUnicode_AsWideCharString(ub, &size);
4838 if (*out)
4839 result = 1;
4840#else
4841 if (!PyUnicode_FSConverter(o, &ub))
4842 return 0;
4843 size = PyBytes_GET_SIZE(ub);
4844 *out = PyMem_Malloc(size + 1);
4845 if (*out) {
4846 memcpy(*out, PyBytes_AS_STRING(ub), size + 1);
4847 result = 1;
4848 } else
4849 PyErr_NoMemory();
4850#endif
4851 Py_DECREF(ub);
4852 return result;
4853}
4854#endif
4855
4856#if defined(HAVE_EXECV) || defined (HAVE_FEXECVE)
4857static EXECV_CHAR**
4858parse_envlist(PyObject* env, Py_ssize_t *envc_ptr)
4859{
4860 Py_ssize_t i, pos, envc;
4861 PyObject *keys=NULL, *vals=NULL;
4862 PyObject *key, *val, *key2, *val2, *keyval;
4863 EXECV_CHAR **envlist;
4864
4865 i = PyMapping_Size(env);
4866 if (i < 0)
4867 return NULL;
4868 envlist = PyMem_NEW(EXECV_CHAR *, i + 1);
4869 if (envlist == NULL) {
4870 PyErr_NoMemory();
4871 return NULL;
4872 }
4873 envc = 0;
4874 keys = PyMapping_Keys(env);
4875 if (!keys)
4876 goto error;
4877 vals = PyMapping_Values(env);
4878 if (!vals)
4879 goto error;
4880 if (!PyList_Check(keys) || !PyList_Check(vals)) {
4881 PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
4882 "env.keys() or env.values() is not a list");
4883 goto error;
4884 }
4885
4886 for (pos = 0; pos < i; pos++) {
4887 key = PyList_GetItem(keys, pos);
4888 val = PyList_GetItem(vals, pos);
4889 if (!key || !val)
4890 goto error;
4891
4892#if defined(HAVE_WEXECV) || defined(HAVE_WSPAWNV)
4893 if (!PyUnicode_FSDecoder(key, &key2))
4894 goto error;
4895 if (!PyUnicode_FSDecoder(val, &val2)) {
4896 Py_DECREF(key2);
4897 goto error;
4898 }
4899 /* Search from index 1 because on Windows starting '=' is allowed for
4900 defining hidden environment variables. */
4901 if (PyUnicode_GET_LENGTH(key2) == 0 ||
4902 PyUnicode_FindChar(key2, '=', 1, PyUnicode_GET_LENGTH(key2), 1) != -1)
4903 {
4904 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError, "illegal environment variable name");
4905 Py_DECREF(key2);
4906 Py_DECREF(val2);
4907 goto error;
4908 }
4909 keyval = PyUnicode_FromFormat("%U=%U", key2, val2);
4910#else
4911 if (!PyUnicode_FSConverter(key, &key2))
4912 goto error;
4913 if (!PyUnicode_FSConverter(val, &val2)) {
4914 Py_DECREF(key2);
4915 goto error;
4916 }
4917 if (PyBytes_GET_SIZE(key2) == 0 ||
4918 strchr(PyBytes_AS_STRING(key2) + 1, '=') != NULL)
4919 {
4920 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError, "illegal environment variable name");
4921 Py_DECREF(key2);
4922 Py_DECREF(val2);
4923 goto error;
4924 }
4925 keyval = PyBytes_FromFormat("%s=%s", PyBytes_AS_STRING(key2),
4926 PyBytes_AS_STRING(val2));
4927#endif
4928 Py_DECREF(key2);
4929 Py_DECREF(val2);
4930 if (!keyval)
4931 goto error;
4932
4933 if (!fsconvert_strdup(keyval, &envlist[envc++])) {
4934 Py_DECREF(keyval);
4935 goto error;
4936 }
4937
4938 Py_DECREF(keyval);
4939 }
4940 Py_DECREF(vals);
4941 Py_DECREF(keys);
4942
4943 envlist[envc] = 0;
4944 *envc_ptr = envc;
4945 return envlist;
4946
4947error:
4948 Py_XDECREF(keys);
4949 Py_XDECREF(vals);
4950 free_string_array(envlist, envc);
4951 return NULL;
4952}
4953
4954static EXECV_CHAR**
4955parse_arglist(PyObject* argv, Py_ssize_t *argc)
4956{
4957 int i;
4958 EXECV_CHAR **argvlist = PyMem_NEW(EXECV_CHAR *, *argc+1);
4959 if (argvlist == NULL) {
4960 PyErr_NoMemory();
4961 return NULL;
4962 }
4963 for (i = 0; i < *argc; i++) {
4964 PyObject* item = PySequence_ITEM(argv, i);
4965 if (item == NULL)
4966 goto fail;
4967 if (!fsconvert_strdup(item, &argvlist[i])) {
4968 Py_DECREF(item);
4969 goto fail;
4970 }
4971 Py_DECREF(item);
4972 }
4973 argvlist[*argc] = NULL;
4974 return argvlist;
4975fail:
4976 *argc = i;
4977 free_string_array(argvlist, *argc);
4978 return NULL;
4979}
4980
4981#endif
4982
4983
4984#ifdef HAVE_EXECV
4985/*[clinic input]
4986os.execv
4987
4988 path: path_t
4989 Path of executable file.
4990 argv: object
4991 Tuple or list of strings.
4992 /
4993
4994Execute an executable path with arguments, replacing current process.
4995[clinic start generated code]*/
4996
4997static PyObject *
4998os_execv_impl(PyObject *module, path_t *path, PyObject *argv)
4999/*[clinic end generated code: output=3b52fec34cd0dafd input=9bac31efae07dac7]*/
5000{
5001 EXECV_CHAR **argvlist;
5002 Py_ssize_t argc;
5003
5004 /* execv has two arguments: (path, argv), where
5005 argv is a list or tuple of strings. */
5006
5007 if (!PyList_Check(argv) && !PyTuple_Check(argv)) {
5008 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
5009 "execv() arg 2 must be a tuple or list");
5010 return NULL;
5011 }
5012 argc = PySequence_Size(argv);
5013 if (argc < 1) {
5014 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError, "execv() arg 2 must not be empty");
5015 return NULL;
5016 }
5017
5018 argvlist = parse_arglist(argv, &argc);
5019 if (argvlist == NULL) {
5020 return NULL;
5021 }
5022 if (!argvlist[0][0]) {
5023 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError,
5024 "execv() arg 2 first element cannot be empty");
5025 free_string_array(argvlist, argc);
5026 return NULL;
5027 }
5028
5029 _Py_BEGIN_SUPPRESS_IPH
5030#ifdef HAVE_WEXECV
5031 _wexecv(path->wide, argvlist);
5032#else
5033 execv(path->narrow, argvlist);
5034#endif
5035 _Py_END_SUPPRESS_IPH
5036
5037 /* If we get here it's definitely an error */
5038
5039 free_string_array(argvlist, argc);
5040 return posix_error();
5041}

5043
5044/*[clinic input]
5045os.execve
5046
5047 path: path_t(allow_fd='PATH_HAVE_FEXECVE')
5048 Path of executable file.
5049 argv: object
5050 Tuple or list of strings.
5051 env: object
5052 Dictionary of strings mapping to strings.
5053
5054Execute an executable path with arguments, replacing current process.
5055[clinic start generated code]*/
5056
5057static PyObject *
5058os_execve_impl(PyObject *module, path_t *path, PyObject *argv, PyObject *env)
5059/*[clinic end generated code: output=ff9fa8e4da8bde58 input=626804fa092606d9]*/
5060{
5061 EXECV_CHAR **argvlist = NULL;
5062 EXECV_CHAR **envlist;
5063 Py_ssize_t argc, envc;
5064
5065 /* execve has three arguments: (path, argv, env), where
5066 argv is a list or tuple of strings and env is a dictionary
5067 like posix.environ. */
5068
5069 if (!PyList_Check(argv) && !PyTuple_Check(argv)) {
5070 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
5071 "execve: argv must be a tuple or list");
5072 goto fail;
5073 }
5074 argc = PySequence_Size(argv);
5075 if (argc < 1) {
5076 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError, "execve: argv must not be empty");
5077 return NULL;
5078 }
5079
5080 if (!PyMapping_Check(env)) {
5081 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
5082 "execve: environment must be a mapping object");
5083 goto fail;
5084 }
5085
5086 argvlist = parse_arglist(argv, &argc);
5087 if (argvlist == NULL) {
5088 goto fail;
5089 }
5090 if (!argvlist[0][0]) {
5091 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError,
5092 "execve: argv first element cannot be empty");
5093 goto fail;
5094 }
5095
5096 envlist = parse_envlist(env, &envc);
5097 if (envlist == NULL)
5098 goto fail;
5099
5100 _Py_BEGIN_SUPPRESS_IPH
5101#ifdef HAVE_FEXECVE
5102 if (path->fd > -1)
5103 fexecve(path->fd, argvlist, envlist);
5104 else
5105#endif
5106#ifdef HAVE_WEXECV
5107 _wexecve(path->wide, argvlist, envlist);
5108#else
5109 execve(path->narrow, argvlist, envlist);
5110#endif
5111 _Py_END_SUPPRESS_IPH
5112
5113 /* If we get here it's definitely an error */
5114
5115 path_error(path);
5116
5117 free_string_array(envlist, envc);
5118 fail:
5119 if (argvlist)
5120 free_string_array(argvlist, argc);
5121 return NULL;
5122}
5123
5124#endif /* HAVE_EXECV */

5335/* Helper function to validate arguments.
5336 Returns 0 on success. non-zero on failure with a TypeError raised.
5337 If obj is non-NULL it must be callable. */
5338static int
5339check_null_or_callable(PyObject *obj, const char* obj_name)
5340{
5341 if (obj && !PyCallable_Check(obj)) {

5349/*[clinic input]
5350os.register_at_fork
5351
5352 *
5353 before: object=NULL
5354 A callable to be called in the parent before the fork() syscall.
5355 after_in_child: object=NULL
5356 A callable to be called in the child after fork().
5357 after_in_parent: object=NULL
5358 A callable to be called in the parent after fork().
5359
5360Register callables to be called when forking a new process.
5361
5362'before' callbacks are called in reverse order.
5363'after_in_child' and 'after_in_parent' callbacks are called in order.
5364
5365[clinic start generated code]*/
5366
5367static PyObject *
5368os_register_at_fork_impl(PyObject *module, PyObject *before,
5369 PyObject *after_in_child, PyObject *after_in_parent)
5370/*[clinic end generated code: output=5398ac75e8e97625 input=cd1187aa85d2312e]*/
5371{
5372 PyInterpreterState *interp;
5373
5374 if (!before && !after_in_child && !after_in_parent) {
5375 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "At least one argument is required.");
5376 return NULL;
5377 }
5378 if (check_null_or_callable(before, "before") ||
5379 check_null_or_callable(after_in_child, "after_in_child") ||
5380 check_null_or_callable(after_in_parent, "after_in_parent")) {
5381 return NULL;
5382 }
5383 interp = PyThreadState_Get()->interp;
5384
5385 if (register_at_forker(&interp->before_forkers, before)) {
5386 return NULL;
5387 }
5388 if (register_at_forker(&interp->after_forkers_child, after_in_child)) {
5389 return NULL;
5390 }
5391 if (register_at_forker(&interp->after_forkers_parent, after_in_parent)) {
5392 return NULL;
5393 }
5394 Py_RETURN_NONE;
5395}
5396#endif /* HAVE_FORK */

5400/*[clinic input]
5401os.fork1
5402
5403Fork a child process with a single multiplexed (i.e., not bound) thread.
5404
5405Return 0 to child process and PID of child to parent process.
5406[clinic start generated code]*/
5407
5408static PyObject *
5409os_fork1_impl(PyObject *module)
5410/*[clinic end generated code: output=0de8e67ce2a310bc input=12db02167893926e]*/
5411{
5412 pid_t pid;
5413
5414 PyOS_BeforeFork();
5415 pid = fork1();
5416 if (pid == 0) {
5417 /* child: this clobbers and resets the import lock. */
5418 PyOS_AfterFork_Child();
5419 } else {
5420 /* parent: release the import lock. */
5421 PyOS_AfterFork_Parent();
5422 }
5423 if (pid == -1)
5424 return posix_error();
5425 return PyLong_FromPid(pid);
5426}
5427#endif /* HAVE_FORK1 */

5567 sched_param_fields,

5570
5571static int
5572convert_sched_param(PyObject *param, struct sched_param *res)
5573{
5574 long priority;
5575
5576 if (Py_TYPE(param) != &SchedParamType) {
5577 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "must have a sched_param object");
5578 return 0;
5579 }
5580 priority = PyLong_AsLong(PyStructSequence_GET_ITEM(param, 0));
5581 if (priority == -1 && PyErr_Occurred())
5582 return 0;
5583 if (priority > INT_MAX || priority < INT_MIN) {
5584 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_OverflowError, "sched_priority out of range");
5585 return 0;
5586 }
5587 res->sched_priority = Py_SAFE_DOWNCAST(priority, long, int);
5588 return 1;
5589}

5724#ifdef HAVE_SCHED_SETAFFINITY
5725/* The minimum number of CPUs allocated in a cpu_set_t */
5726static const int NCPUS_START = sizeof(unsigned long) * CHAR_BIT;
5727
5728/*[clinic input]
5729os.sched_setaffinity
5730 pid: pid_t
5731 mask : object
5732 /
5733
5734Set the CPU affinity of the process identified by pid to mask.
5735
5736mask should be an iterable of integers identifying CPUs.
5737[clinic start generated code]*/
5738
5739static PyObject *
5740os_sched_setaffinity_impl(PyObject *module, pid_t pid, PyObject *mask)
5741/*[clinic end generated code: output=882d7dd9a229335b input=a0791a597c7085ba]*/
5742{
5743 int ncpus;
5744 size_t setsize;
5745 cpu_set_t *cpu_set = NULL;
5746 PyObject *iterator = NULL, *item;
5747
5748 iterator = PyObject_GetIter(mask);
5749 if (iterator == NULL)
5750 return NULL;
5751
5752 ncpus = NCPUS_START;
5753 setsize = CPU_ALLOC_SIZE(ncpus);
5754 cpu_set = CPU_ALLOC(ncpus);
5755 if (cpu_set == NULL) {
5756 PyErr_NoMemory();
5757 goto error;
5758 }
5759 CPU_ZERO_S(setsize, cpu_set);
5760
5761 while ((item = PyIter_Next(iterator))) {
5762 long cpu;
5763 if (!PyLong_Check(item)) {
5764 PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
5765 "expected an iterator of ints, "
5766 "but iterator yielded %R",
5767 Py_TYPE(item));
5768 Py_DECREF(item);
5769 goto error;
5770 }
5771 cpu = PyLong_AsLong(item);
5772 Py_DECREF(item);
5773 if (cpu < 0) {
5774 if (!PyErr_Occurred())
5775 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError, "negative CPU number");
5776 goto error;
5777 }
5778 if (cpu > INT_MAX - 1) {
5779 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_OverflowError, "CPU number too large");
5780 goto error;
5781 }
5782 if (cpu >= ncpus) {
5783 /* Grow CPU mask to fit the CPU number */
5784 int newncpus = ncpus;
5785 cpu_set_t *newmask;
5786 size_t newsetsize;
5787 while (newncpus <= cpu) {
5788 if (newncpus > INT_MAX / 2)
5789 newncpus = cpu + 1;
5790 else
5791 newncpus = newncpus * 2;
5792 }
5793 newmask = CPU_ALLOC(newncpus);
5794 if (newmask == NULL) {
5795 PyErr_NoMemory();
5796 goto error;
5797 }
5798 newsetsize = CPU_ALLOC_SIZE(newncpus);
5799 CPU_ZERO_S(newsetsize, newmask);
5800 memcpy(newmask, cpu_set, setsize);
5801 CPU_FREE(cpu_set);
5802 setsize = newsetsize;
5803 cpu_set = newmask;
5804 ncpus = newncpus;
5805 }
5806 CPU_SET_S(cpu, setsize, cpu_set);
5807 }
5808 Py_CLEAR(iterator);
5809
5810 if (sched_setaffinity(pid, setsize, cpu_set)) {
5811 posix_error();
5812 goto error;
5813 }
5814 CPU_FREE(cpu_set);
5815 Py_RETURN_NONE;
5816
5817error:
5818 if (cpu_set)
5819 CPU_FREE(cpu_set);
5820 Py_XDECREF(iterator);
5821 return NULL;
5822}
5823
5824
5825/*[clinic input]
5826os.sched_getaffinity
5827 pid: pid_t
5828 /
5829
5830Return the affinity of the process identified by pid (or the current process if zero).
5831
5832The affinity is returned as a set of CPU identifiers.
5833[clinic start generated code]*/
5834
5835static PyObject *
5836os_sched_getaffinity_impl(PyObject *module, pid_t pid)
5837/*[clinic end generated code: output=f726f2c193c17a4f input=983ce7cb4a565980]*/
5838{
5839 int cpu, ncpus, count;
5840 size_t setsize;
5841 cpu_set_t *mask = NULL;
5842 PyObject *res = NULL;
5843
5844 ncpus = NCPUS_START;
5845 while (1) {
5846 setsize = CPU_ALLOC_SIZE(ncpus);
5847 mask = CPU_ALLOC(ncpus);
5848 if (mask == NULL)
5849 return PyErr_NoMemory();
5850 if (sched_getaffinity(pid, setsize, mask) == 0)
5851 break;
5852 CPU_FREE(mask);
5853 if (errno != EINVAL)
5854 return posix_error();
5855 if (ncpus > INT_MAX / 2) {
5856 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_OverflowError, "could not allocate "
5857 "a large enough CPU set");
5858 return NULL;
5859 }
5860 ncpus = ncpus * 2;
5861 }
5862
5863 res = PySet_New(NULL);
5864 if (res == NULL)
5865 goto error;
5866 for (cpu = 0, count = CPU_COUNT_S(setsize, mask); count; cpu++) {
5867 if (CPU_ISSET_S(cpu, setsize, mask)) {
5868 PyObject *cpu_num = PyLong_FromLong(cpu);
5869 --count;
5870 if (cpu_num == NULL)
5871 goto error;
5872 if (PySet_Add(res, cpu_num)) {
5873 Py_DECREF(cpu_num);
5874 goto error;
5875 }
5876 Py_DECREF(cpu_num);
5877 }
5878 }
5879 CPU_FREE(mask);
5880 return res;
5881
5882error:
5883 if (mask)
5884 CPU_FREE(mask);
5885 Py_XDECREF(res);
5886 return NULL;
5887}
5888
5889#endif /* HAVE_SCHED_SETAFFINITY */
5890
5891#endif /* HAVE_SCHED_H */

5894/* AIX uses /dev/ptc but is otherwise the same as /dev/ptmx */
5895/* IRIX has both /dev/ptc and /dev/ptmx, use ptmx */
5896#if defined(HAVE_DEV_PTC) && !defined(HAVE_DEV_PTMX)
5897#define DEV_PTY_FILE "/dev/ptc"
5898#define HAVE_DEV_PTMX
5899#else
5900#define DEV_PTY_FILE "/dev/ptmx"
5901#endif
5902
5903#if defined(HAVE_OPENPTY) || defined(HAVE_FORKPTY) || defined(HAVE_DEV_PTMX)
5904#ifdef HAVE_PTY_H
5905#include <pty.h>
5906#else
5907#ifdef HAVE_LIBUTIL_H
5908#include <libutil.h>
5909#else
5910#ifdef HAVE_UTIL_H
5911#include <util.h>
5912#endif /* HAVE_UTIL_H */
5913#endif /* HAVE_LIBUTIL_H */
5914#endif /* HAVE_PTY_H */
5915#ifdef HAVE_STROPTS_H
5916#include <stropts.h>
5917#endif
5918#endif /* defined(HAVE_OPENPTY) || defined(HAVE_FORKPTY) || defined(HAVE_DEV_PTMX */
5919
5920
5921#if defined(HAVE_OPENPTY) || defined(HAVE__GETPTY) || defined(HAVE_DEV_PTMX)
5922/*[clinic input]
5923os.openpty
5924
5925Open a pseudo-terminal.
5926
5927Return a tuple of (master_fd, slave_fd) containing open file descriptors
5928for both the master and slave ends.
5929[clinic start generated code]*/
5930
5931static PyObject *
5932os_openpty_impl(PyObject *module)
5933/*[clinic end generated code: output=98841ce5ec9cef3c input=f3d99fd99e762907]*/
5934{
5935 int master_fd = -1, slave_fd = -1;
5936#ifndef HAVE_OPENPTY
5937 char * slave_name;
5938#endif
5939#if defined(HAVE_DEV_PTMX) && !defined(HAVE_OPENPTY) && !defined(HAVE__GETPTY)
5940 PyOS_sighandler_t sig_saved;
5941#ifdef sun
5942 extern char *ptsname(int fildes);
5943#endif
5944#endif
5945
5946#ifdef HAVE_OPENPTY
5947 if (openpty(&master_fd, &slave_fd, NULL, NULL, NULL) != 0)
5948 goto posix_error;
5949
5950 if (_Py_set_inheritable(master_fd, 0, NULL) < 0)
5951 goto error;
5952 if (_Py_set_inheritable(slave_fd, 0, NULL) < 0)
5953 goto error;
5954
5955#elif defined(HAVE__GETPTY)
5956 slave_name = _getpty(&master_fd, O_RDWR, 0666, 0);
5957 if (slave_name == NULL)
5958 goto posix_error;
5959 if (_Py_set_inheritable(master_fd, 0, NULL) < 0)
5960 goto error;
5961
5962 slave_fd = _Py_open(slave_name, O_RDWR);
5963 if (slave_fd < 0)
5964 goto error;
5965
5966#else
5967 master_fd = open(DEV_PTY_FILE, O_RDWR | O_NOCTTY); /* open master */
5968 if (master_fd < 0)
5969 goto posix_error;
5970
5971 sig_saved = PyOS_setsig(SIGCHLD, SIG_DFL);
5972
5973 /* change permission of slave */
5974 if (grantpt(master_fd) < 0) {
5975 PyOS_setsig(SIGCHLD, sig_saved);
5976 goto posix_error;
5977 }
5978
5979 /* unlock slave */
5980 if (unlockpt(master_fd) < 0) {
5981 PyOS_setsig(SIGCHLD, sig_saved);
5982 goto posix_error;
5983 }
5984
5985 PyOS_setsig(SIGCHLD, sig_saved);
5986
5987 slave_name = ptsname(master_fd); /* get name of slave */
5988 if (slave_name == NULL)
5989 goto posix_error;
5990
5991 slave_fd = _Py_open(slave_name, O_RDWR | O_NOCTTY); /* open slave */
5992 if (slave_fd == -1)
5993 goto error;
5994
5995 if (_Py_set_inheritable(master_fd, 0, NULL) < 0)
5996 goto posix_error;
5997
5998#if !defined(__CYGWIN__) && !defined(__ANDROID__) && !defined(HAVE_DEV_PTC)
5999 ioctl(slave_fd, I_PUSH, "ptem"); /* push ptem */
6000 ioctl(slave_fd, I_PUSH, "ldterm"); /* push ldterm */
6001#ifndef __hpux
6002 ioctl(slave_fd, I_PUSH, "ttcompat"); /* push ttcompat */
6003#endif /* __hpux */
6004#endif /* HAVE_CYGWIN */
6005#endif /* HAVE_OPENPTY */
6006
6007 return Py_BuildValue("(ii)", master_fd, slave_fd);
6008
6009posix_error:
6010 posix_error();
6011error:
6012 if (master_fd != -1)
6013 close(master_fd);
6014 if (slave_fd != -1)
6015 close(slave_fd);
6016 return NULL;
6017}
6018#endif /* defined(HAVE_OPENPTY) || defined(HAVE__GETPTY) || defined(HAVE_DEV_PTMX) */
6019
6020
6021#ifdef HAVE_FORKPTY
6022/*[clinic input]
6023os.forkpty
6024
6025Fork a new process with a new pseudo-terminal as controlling tty.
6026
6027Returns a tuple of (pid, master_fd).
6028Like fork(), return pid of 0 to the child process,
6029and pid of child to the parent process.
6030To both, return fd of newly opened pseudo-terminal.
6031[clinic start generated code]*/
6032
6033static PyObject *
6034os_forkpty_impl(PyObject *module)
6035/*[clinic end generated code: output=60d0a5c7512e4087 input=f1f7f4bae3966010]*/
6036{
6037 int master_fd = -1;
6038 pid_t pid;
6039
6040 PyOS_BeforeFork();
6041 pid = forkpty(&master_fd, NULL, NULL, NULL);
6042 if (pid == 0) {
6043 /* child: this clobbers and resets the import lock. */
6044 PyOS_AfterFork_Child();
6045 } else {
6046 /* parent: release the import lock. */
6047 PyOS_AfterFork_Parent();
6048 }
6049 if (pid == -1)
6050 return posix_error();
6051 return Py_BuildValue("(Ni)", PyLong_FromPid(pid), master_fd);
6052}
6053#endif /* HAVE_FORKPTY */

6120
6121/* AC 3.5: funny apple logic below */
6122PyDoc_STRVAR(posix_getgrouplist__doc__,
6123"getgrouplist(user, group) -> list of groups to which a user belongs\n\n\
6124Returns a list of groups to which a user belongs.\n\n\
6125 user: username to lookup\n\
6126 group: base group id of the user");
6127
6128static PyObject *
6129posix_getgrouplist(PyObject *self, PyObject *args)
6130{
6131#ifdef NGROUPS_MAX
6132#define MAX_GROUPS NGROUPS_MAX
6133#else
6134 /* defined to be 16 on Solaris7, so this should be a small number */
6135#define MAX_GROUPS 64
6136#endif
6137
6138 const char *user;
6139 int i, ngroups;
6140 PyObject *list;
6141#ifdef __APPLE__
6142 int *groups, basegid;
6143#else
6144 gid_t *groups, basegid;
6145#endif
6146 ngroups = MAX_GROUPS;
6147
6148#ifdef __APPLE__
6149 if (!PyArg_ParseTuple(args, "si:getgrouplist", &user, &basegid))
6150 return NULL;
6151#else
6152 if (!PyArg_ParseTuple(args, "sO&:getgrouplist", &user,
6153 _Py_Gid_Converter, &basegid))
6154 return NULL;
6155#endif
6156
6157#ifdef __APPLE__
6158 groups = PyMem_New(int, ngroups);
6159#else
6160 groups = PyMem_New(gid_t, ngroups);
6161#endif
6162 if (groups == NULL)
6163 return PyErr_NoMemory();
6164
6165 if (getgrouplist(user, basegid, groups, &ngroups) == -1) {
6166 PyMem_Del(groups);
6167 return posix_error();
6168 }
6169
6170 list = PyList_New(ngroups);
6171 if (list == NULL) {
6172 PyMem_Del(groups);
6173 return NULL;
6174 }
6175
6176 for (i = 0; i < ngroups; i++) {
6177#ifdef __APPLE__
6178 PyObject *o = PyLong_FromUnsignedLong((unsigned long)groups[i]);
6179#else
6180 PyObject *o = _PyLong_FromGid(groups[i]);
6181#endif
6182 if (o == NULL) {
6183 Py_DECREF(list);
6184 PyMem_Del(groups);
6185 return NULL;
6186 }
6187 PyList_SET_ITEM(list, i, o);
6188 }
6189
6190 PyMem_Del(groups);
6191
6192 return list;
6193}
6194#endif /* HAVE_GETGROUPLIST */

6196
6197#ifdef HAVE_GETGROUPS
6198/*[clinic input]
6199os.getgroups
6200
6201Return list of supplemental group IDs for the process.
6202[clinic start generated code]*/
6203
6204static PyObject *
6205os_getgroups_impl(PyObject *module)
6206/*[clinic end generated code: output=42b0c17758561b56 input=d3f109412e6a155c]*/
6207{
6208 PyObject *result = NULL;
6209
6210#ifdef NGROUPS_MAX
6211#define MAX_GROUPS NGROUPS_MAX
6212#else
6213 /* defined to be 16 on Solaris7, so this should be a small number */
6214#define MAX_GROUPS 64
6215#endif
6216 gid_t grouplist[MAX_GROUPS];
6217
6218 /* On MacOSX getgroups(2) can return more than MAX_GROUPS results
6219 * This is a helper variable to store the intermediate result when
6220 * that happens.
6221 *
6222 * To keep the code readable the OSX behaviour is unconditional,
6223 * according to the POSIX spec this should be safe on all unix-y
6224 * systems.
6225 */
6226 gid_t* alt_grouplist = grouplist;
6227 int n;
6228
6229#ifdef __APPLE__
6230 /* Issue #17557: As of OS X 10.8, getgroups(2) no longer raises EINVAL if
6231 * there are more groups than can fit in grouplist. Therefore, on OS X
6232 * always first call getgroups with length 0 to get the actual number
6233 * of groups.
6234 */
6235 n = getgroups(0, NULL);
6236 if (n < 0) {
6237 return posix_error();
6238 } else if (n <= MAX_GROUPS) {
6239 /* groups will fit in existing array */
6240 alt_grouplist = grouplist;
6241 } else {
6242 alt_grouplist = PyMem_New(gid_t, n);
6243 if (alt_grouplist == NULL) {
6244 errno = EINVAL;
6245 return posix_error();
6246 }
6247 }
6248
6249 n = getgroups(n, alt_grouplist);
6250 if (n == -1) {
6251 if (alt_grouplist != grouplist) {
6252 PyMem_Free(alt_grouplist);
6253 }
6254 return posix_error();
6255 }
6256#else
6257 n = getgroups(MAX_GROUPS, grouplist);
6258 if (n < 0) {
6259 if (errno == EINVAL) {
6260 n = getgroups(0, NULL);
6261 if (n == -1) {
6262 return posix_error();
6263 }
6264 if (n == 0) {
6265 /* Avoid malloc(0) */
6266 alt_grouplist = grouplist;
6267 } else {
6268 alt_grouplist = PyMem_New(gid_t, n);
6269 if (alt_grouplist == NULL) {
6270 errno = EINVAL;
6271 return posix_error();
6272 }
6273 n = getgroups(n, alt_grouplist);
6274 if (n == -1) {
6275 PyMem_Free(alt_grouplist);
6276 return posix_error();
6277 }
6278 }
6279 } else {
6280 return posix_error();
6281 }
6282 }
6283#endif
6284
6285 result = PyList_New(n);
6286 if (result != NULL) {
6287 int i;
6288 for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
6289 PyObject *o = _PyLong_FromGid(alt_grouplist[i]);
6290 if (o == NULL) {
6291 Py_DECREF(result);
6292 result = NULL;
6293 break;
6294 }
6295 PyList_SET_ITEM(result, i, o);
6296 }
6297 }
6298
6299 if (alt_grouplist != grouplist) {
6300 PyMem_Free(alt_grouplist);
6301 }
6302
6303 return result;
6304}
6305#endif /* HAVE_GETGROUPS */

6411#ifdef HAVE_GETPPID
6412
6413#ifdef MS_WINDOWS
6414#include <tlhelp32.h>
6415
6416static PyObject*
6417win32_getppid()
6418{
6419 HANDLE snapshot;
6420 pid_t mypid;
6421 PyObject* result = NULL;
6422 BOOL have_record;
6423 PROCESSENTRY32 pe;
6424
6425 mypid = getpid(); /* This function never fails */
6426
6427 snapshot = CreateToolhelp32Snapshot(TH32CS_SNAPPROCESS, 0);
6428 if (snapshot == INVALID_HANDLE_VALUE)
6429 return PyErr_SetFromWindowsErr(GetLastError());
6430
6431 pe.dwSize = sizeof(pe);
6432 have_record = Process32First(snapshot, &pe);
6433 while (have_record) {
6434 if (mypid == (pid_t)pe.th32ProcessID) {
6435 /* We could cache the ulong value in a static variable. */
6436 result = PyLong_FromPid((pid_t)pe.th32ParentProcessID);
6437 break;
6438 }
6439
6440 have_record = Process32Next(snapshot, &pe);
6441 }
6442
6443 /* If our loop exits and our pid was not found (result will be NULL)
6444 * then GetLastError will return ERROR_NO_MORE_FILES. This is an
6445 * error anyway, so let's raise it. */
6446 if (!result)
6447 result = PyErr_SetFromWindowsErr(GetLastError());
6448
6449 CloseHandle(snapshot);
6450
6451 return result;
6452}
6453#endif /*MS_WINDOWS*/

6478#ifdef HAVE_GETLOGIN
6479/*[clinic input]
6480os.getlogin
6481
6482Return the actual login name.
6483[clinic start generated code]*/
6484
6485static PyObject *
6486os_getlogin_impl(PyObject *module)
6487/*[clinic end generated code: output=a32e66a7e5715dac input=2a21ab1e917163df]*/
6488{
6489 PyObject *result = NULL;
6490#ifdef MS_WINDOWS
6491 wchar_t user_name[UNLEN + 1];
6492 DWORD num_chars = Py_ARRAY_LENGTH(user_name);
6493
6494 if (GetUserNameW(user_name, &num_chars)) {
6495 /* num_chars is the number of unicode chars plus null terminator */
6496 result = PyUnicode_FromWideChar(user_name, num_chars - 1);
6497 }
6498 else
6499 result = PyErr_SetFromWindowsErr(GetLastError());
6500#else
6501 char *name;
6502 int old_errno = errno;
6503
6504 errno = 0;
6505 name = getlogin();
6506 if (name == NULL) {
6507 if (errno)
6508 posix_error();
6509 else
6510 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_OSError, "unable to determine login name");
6511 }
6512 else
6513 result = PyUnicode_DecodeFSDefault(name);
6514 errno = old_errno;
6515#endif
6516 return result;

6540
6541#ifdef HAVE_KILL
6542/*[clinic input]
6543os.kill
6544
6545 pid: pid_t
6546 signal: Py_ssize_t
6547 /
6548
6549Kill a process with a signal.
6550[clinic start generated code]*/
6551
6552static PyObject *
6553os_kill_impl(PyObject *module, pid_t pid, Py_ssize_t signal)
6554/*[clinic end generated code: output=8e346a6701c88568 input=61a36b86ca275ab9]*/
6555#ifndef MS_WINDOWS
6556{
6557 if (kill(pid, (int)signal) == -1)
6558 return posix_error();
6559 Py_RETURN_NONE;
6560}
6561#else /* !MS_WINDOWS */
6562{
6563 PyObject *result;
6564 DWORD sig = (DWORD)signal;
6565 DWORD err;
6566 HANDLE handle;
6567
6568 /* Console processes which share a common console can be sent CTRL+C or
6569 CTRL+BREAK events, provided they handle said events. */
6570 if (sig == CTRL_C_EVENT || sig == CTRL_BREAK_EVENT) {
6571 if (GenerateConsoleCtrlEvent(sig, (DWORD)pid) == 0) {
6572 err = GetLastError();
6573 PyErr_SetFromWindowsErr(err);
6574 }
6575 else
6576 Py_RETURN_NONE;
6577 }
6578
6579 /* If the signal is outside of what GenerateConsoleCtrlEvent can use,
6580 attempt to open and terminate the process. */
6581 handle = OpenProcess(PROCESS_ALL_ACCESS, FALSE, (DWORD)pid);
6582 if (handle == NULL) {
6583 err = GetLastError();
6584 return PyErr_SetFromWindowsErr(err);
6585 }
6586
6587 if (TerminateProcess(handle, sig) == 0) {
6588 err = GetLastError();
6589 result = PyErr_SetFromWindowsErr(err);
6590 } else {
6591 Py_INCREF(Py_None);
6592 result = Py_None;
6593 }
6594
6595 CloseHandle(handle);
6596 return result;
6597}
6598#endif /* !MS_WINDOWS */
6599#endif /* HAVE_KILL */

6781#ifdef HAVE_SETGROUPS
6782/*[clinic input]
6783os.setgroups
6784
6785 groups: object
6786 /
6787
6788Set the groups of the current process to list.
6789[clinic start generated code]*/
6790
6791static PyObject *
6792os_setgroups(PyObject *module, PyObject *groups)
6793/*[clinic end generated code: output=3fcb32aad58c5ecd input=fa742ca3daf85a7e]*/
6794{
6795 Py_ssize_t i, len;
6796 gid_t grouplist[MAX_GROUPS];
6797
6798 if (!PySequence_Check(groups)) {
6799 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "setgroups argument must be a sequence");
6800 return NULL;
6801 }
6802 len = PySequence_Size(groups);
6803 if (len < 0) {
6804 return NULL;
6805 }
6806 if (len > MAX_GROUPS) {
6807 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError, "too many groups");
6808 return NULL;
6809 }
6810 for(i = 0; i < len; i++) {
6811 PyObject *elem;
6812 elem = PySequence_GetItem(groups, i);
6813 if (!elem)
6814 return NULL;
6815 if (!PyLong_Check(elem)) {
6816 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
6817 "groups must be integers");
6818 Py_DECREF(elem);
6819 return NULL;
6820 } else {
6821 if (!_Py_Gid_Converter(elem, &grouplist[i])) {
6822 Py_DECREF(elem);
6823 return NULL;
6824 }
6825 }
6826 Py_DECREF(elem);
6827 }
6828
6829 if (setgroups(len, grouplist) < 0)
6830 return posix_error();
6831 Py_RETURN_NONE;
6832}
6833#endif /* HAVE_SETGROUPS */
6834
6835#if defined(HAVE_WAIT3) || defined(HAVE_WAIT4)
6836static PyObject *
6837wait_helper(pid_t pid, int status, struct rusage *ru)
6838{
6839 PyObject *result;
6840 static PyObject *struct_rusage;
6841 _Py_IDENTIFIER(struct_rusage);
6842
6843 if (pid == -1)
6844 return posix_error();
6845
6846 if (struct_rusage == NULL) {
6847 PyObject *m = PyImport_ImportModuleNoBlock("resource");
6848 if (m == NULL)
6849 return NULL;
6850 struct_rusage = _PyObject_GetAttrId(m, &PyId_struct_rusage);
6851 Py_DECREF(m);
6852 if (struct_rusage == NULL)
6853 return NULL;
6854 }
6855
6856 /* XXX(nnorwitz): Copied (w/mods) from resource.c, there should be only one. */
6857 result = PyStructSequence_New((PyTypeObject*) struct_rusage);
6858 if (!result)
6859 return NULL;
6860
6861#ifndef doubletime
6862#define doubletime(TV) ((double)(TV).tv_sec + (TV).tv_usec * 0.000001)
6863#endif
6864
6865 PyStructSequence_SET_ITEM(result, 0,
6866 PyFloat_FromDouble(doubletime(ru->ru_utime)));
6867 PyStructSequence_SET_ITEM(result, 1,
6868 PyFloat_FromDouble(doubletime(ru->ru_stime)));
6869#define SET_INT(result, index, value)\
6870 PyStructSequence_SET_ITEM(result, index, PyLong_FromLong(value))
6871 SET_INT(result, 2, ru->ru_maxrss);
6872 SET_INT(result, 3, ru->ru_ixrss);
6873 SET_INT(result, 4, ru->ru_idrss);
6874 SET_INT(result, 5, ru->ru_isrss);
6875 SET_INT(result, 6, ru->ru_minflt);
6876 SET_INT(result, 7, ru->ru_majflt);
6877 SET_INT(result, 8, ru->ru_nswap);
6878 SET_INT(result, 9, ru->ru_inblock);
6879 SET_INT(result, 10, ru->ru_oublock);
6880 SET_INT(result, 11, ru->ru_msgsnd);
6881 SET_INT(result, 12, ru->ru_msgrcv);
6882 SET_INT(result, 13, ru->ru_nsignals);
6883 SET_INT(result, 14, ru->ru_nvcsw);
6884 SET_INT(result, 15, ru->ru_nivcsw);
6885#undef SET_INT
6886
6887 if (PyErr_Occurred()) {
6888 Py_DECREF(result);
6889 return NULL;
6890 }
6891
6892 return Py_BuildValue("NiN", PyLong_FromPid(pid), status, result);
6893}
6894#endif /* HAVE_WAIT3 || HAVE_WAIT4 */

6897#ifdef HAVE_WAIT3
6898/*[clinic input]
6899os.wait3
6900
6901 options: int
6902Wait for completion of a child process.
6903
6904Returns a tuple of information about the child process:
6905 (pid, status, rusage)
6906[clinic start generated code]*/
6907
6908static PyObject *
6909os_wait3_impl(PyObject *module, int options)
6910/*[clinic end generated code: output=92c3224e6f28217a input=8ac4c56956b61710]*/
6911{
6912 pid_t pid;
6913 struct rusage ru;
6914 int async_err = 0;
6915 WAIT_TYPE status;
6916 WAIT_STATUS_INT(status) = 0;
6917
6918 do {
6919 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
6920 pid = wait3(&status, options, &ru);
6921 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
6922 } while (pid < 0 && errno == EINTR && !(async_err = PyErr_CheckSignals()));
6923 if (pid < 0)
6924 return (!async_err) ? posix_error() : NULL;
6925
6926 return wait_helper(pid, WAIT_STATUS_INT(status), &ru);
6927}
6928#endif /* HAVE_WAIT3 */

6968#if defined(HAVE_WAITID) && !defined(__APPLE__)
6969/*[clinic input]
6970os.waitid
6971
6972 idtype: idtype_t
6973 Must be one of be P_PID, P_PGID or P_ALL.
6974 id: id_t
6975 The id to wait on.
6976 options: int
6977 Constructed from the ORing of one or more of WEXITED, WSTOPPED
6978 or WCONTINUED and additionally may be ORed with WNOHANG or WNOWAIT.
6979 /
6980
6981Returns the result of waiting for a process or processes.
6982
6983Returns either waitid_result or None if WNOHANG is specified and there are
6984no children in a waitable state.
6985[clinic start generated code]*/
6986
6987static PyObject *
6988os_waitid_impl(PyObject *module, idtype_t idtype, id_t id, int options)
6989/*[clinic end generated code: output=5d2e1c0bde61f4d8 input=d8e7f76e052b7920]*/
6990{
6991 PyObject *result;
6992 int res;
6993 int async_err = 0;
6994 siginfo_t si;
6995 si.si_pid = 0;
6996
6997 do {
6998 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
6999 res = waitid(idtype, id, &si, options);
7000 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
7001 } while (res < 0 && errno == EINTR && !(async_err = PyErr_CheckSignals()));
7002 if (res < 0)
7003 return (!async_err) ? posix_error() : NULL;
7004
7005 if (si.si_pid == 0)
7006 Py_RETURN_NONE;
7007
7008 result = PyStructSequence_New(&WaitidResultType);
7009 if (!result)
7010 return NULL;
7011
7012 PyStructSequence_SET_ITEM(result, 0, PyLong_FromPid(si.si_pid));
7013 PyStructSequence_SET_ITEM(result, 1, _PyLong_FromUid(si.si_uid));
7014 PyStructSequence_SET_ITEM(result, 2, PyLong_FromLong((long)(si.si_signo)));
7015 PyStructSequence_SET_ITEM(result, 3, PyLong_FromLong((long)(si.si_status)));
7016 PyStructSequence_SET_ITEM(result, 4, PyLong_FromLong((long)(si.si_code)));
7017 if (PyErr_Occurred()) {
7018 Py_DECREF(result);
7019 return NULL;
7020 }
7021
7022 return result;
7023}
7024#endif /* defined(HAVE_WAITID) && !defined(__APPLE__) */

7062/* MS C has a variant of waitpid() that's usable for most purposes. */
7063/*[clinic input]
7064os.waitpid
7065 pid: intptr_t
7066 options: int
7067 /
7068
7069Wait for completion of a given process.
7070
7071Returns a tuple of information regarding the process:
7072 (pid, status << 8)
7073
7074The options argument is ignored on Windows.
7075[clinic start generated code]*/
7076
7077static PyObject *
7078os_waitpid_impl(PyObject *module, intptr_t pid, int options)
7079/*[clinic end generated code: output=be836b221271d538 input=40f2440c515410f8]*/
7080{

7083 int async_err = 0;

7088 res = _cwait(&status, pid, options);
7089 _Py_END_SUPPRESS_IPH
7090 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS

7096 return Py_BuildValue(_Py_PARSE_INTPTR "i", res, status << 8);

7133#if defined(HAVE_READLINK) || defined(MS_WINDOWS)
7134PyDoc_STRVAR(readlink__doc__,
7135"readlink(path, *, dir_fd=None) -> path\n\n\
7136Return a string representing the path to which the symbolic link points.\n\
7137\n\
7138If dir_fd is not None, it should be a file descriptor open to a directory,\n\
7139 and path should be relative; path will then be relative to that directory.\n\
7140dir_fd may not be implemented on your platform.\n\
7141 If it is unavailable, using it will raise a NotImplementedError.");
7142#endif
7143
7144#ifdef HAVE_READLINK
7145
7146/* AC 3.5: merge win32 and not together */
7147static PyObject *
7148posix_readlink(PyObject *self, PyObject *args, PyObject *kwargs)
7149{
7150 path_t path;
7151 int dir_fd = DEFAULT_DIR_FD;
7152 char buffer[MAXPATHLEN+1];
7153 ssize_t length;
7154 PyObject *return_value = NULL;
7155 static char *keywords[] = {"path", "dir_fd", NULL};
7156
7157 memset(&path, 0, sizeof(path));
7158 path.function_name = "readlink";
7159 if (!PyArg_ParseTupleAndKeywords(args, kwargs, "O&|$O&:readlink", keywords,
7160 path_converter, &path,
7161 READLINKAT_DIR_FD_CONVERTER, &dir_fd))
7162 return NULL;
7163
7164 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
7165#ifdef HAVE_READLINKAT
7166 if (dir_fd != DEFAULT_DIR_FD)
7167 length = readlinkat(dir_fd, path.narrow, buffer, MAXPATHLEN);
7168 else
7169#endif
7170 length = readlink(path.narrow, buffer, MAXPATHLEN);
7171 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
7172
7173 if (length < 0) {
7174 return_value = path_error(&path);
7175 goto exit;
7176 }
7177 buffer[length] = '\0';
7178
7179 if (PyUnicode_Check(path.object))
7180 return_value = PyUnicode_DecodeFSDefaultAndSize(buffer, length);
7181 else
7182 return_value = PyBytes_FromStringAndSize(buffer, length);
7183exit:
7184 path_cleanup(&path);
7185 return return_value;
7186}
7187
7188#endif /* HAVE_READLINK */
7189
7190#if !defined(HAVE_READLINK) && defined(MS_WINDOWS)
7191
7192static PyObject *
7193win_readlink(PyObject *self, PyObject *args, PyObject *kwargs)
7194{
7195 const wchar_t *path;
7196 DWORD n_bytes_returned;
7197 DWORD io_result;
7198 PyObject *po, *result;
7199 int dir_fd;
7200 HANDLE reparse_point_handle;
7201
7202 char target_buffer[_Py_MAXIMUM_REPARSE_DATA_BUFFER_SIZE];
7203 _Py_REPARSE_DATA_BUFFER *rdb = (_Py_REPARSE_DATA_BUFFER *)target_buffer;
7204 const wchar_t *print_name;
7205
7206 static char *keywords[] = {"path", "dir_fd", NULL};
7207
7208 if (!PyArg_ParseTupleAndKeywords(args, kwargs, "U|$O&:readlink", keywords,
7209 &po,
7210 dir_fd_unavailable, &dir_fd
7211 ))
7212 return NULL;
7213
7214 path = _PyUnicode_AsUnicode(po);
7215 if (path == NULL)
7216 return NULL;
7217
7218 /* First get a handle to the reparse point */
7219 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
7220 reparse_point_handle = CreateFileW(
7221 path,
7222 0,
7223 0,
7224 0,
7225 OPEN_EXISTING,
7226 FILE_FLAG_OPEN_REPARSE_POINT|FILE_FLAG_BACKUP_SEMANTICS,
7227 0);
7228 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
7229
7230 if (reparse_point_handle==INVALID_HANDLE_VALUE)
7231 return win32_error_object("readlink", po);
7232
7233 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
7234 /* New call DeviceIoControl to read the reparse point */
7235 io_result = DeviceIoControl(
7236 reparse_point_handle,
7237 FSCTL_GET_REPARSE_POINT,
7238 0, 0, /* in buffer */
7239 target_buffer, sizeof(target_buffer),
7240 &n_bytes_returned,
7241 0 /* we're not using OVERLAPPED_IO */
7242 );
7243 CloseHandle(reparse_point_handle);
7244 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
7245
7246 if (io_result==0)
7247 return win32_error_object("readlink", po);
7248
7249 if (rdb->ReparseTag != IO_REPARSE_TAG_SYMLINK)
7250 {
7251 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError,
7252 "not a symbolic link");
7253 return NULL;
7254 }
7255 print_name = rdb->SymbolicLinkReparseBuffer.PathBuffer +
7256 rdb->SymbolicLinkReparseBuffer.PrintNameOffset;
7257
7258 result = PyUnicode_FromWideChar(print_name,
7259 rdb->SymbolicLinkReparseBuffer.PrintNameLength/2);
7260 return result;
7261}
7262
7263#endif /* !defined(HAVE_READLINK) && defined(MS_WINDOWS) */
7264

7267#ifdef HAVE_SYMLINK
7268
7269#if defined(MS_WINDOWS)

7271/* Grab CreateSymbolicLinkW dynamically from kernel32 */
7272static DWORD (CALLBACK *Py_CreateSymbolicLinkW)(LPCWSTR, LPCWSTR, DWORD) = NULL;
7273
7274static int
7275check_CreateSymbolicLink(void)
7276{
7277 HINSTANCE hKernel32;
7278 /* only recheck */
7279 if (Py_CreateSymbolicLinkW)
7280 return 1;
7281 hKernel32 = GetModuleHandleW(L"KERNEL32");
7282 *(FARPROC*)&Py_CreateSymbolicLinkW = GetProcAddress(hKernel32,
7283 "CreateSymbolicLinkW");
7284 return Py_CreateSymbolicLinkW != NULL;
7285}
7286
7287/* Remove the last portion of the path */
7288static void
7289_dirnameW(WCHAR *path)
7290{
7291 WCHAR *ptr;
7292
7293 /* walk the path from the end until a backslash is encountered */
7294 for(ptr = path + wcslen(path); ptr != path; ptr--) {
7295 if (*ptr == L'\\' || *ptr == L'/')
7296 break;
7297 }
7298 *ptr = 0;
7299}
7300
7301/* Is this path absolute? */
7302static int
7303_is_absW(const WCHAR *path)
7304{
7305 return path[0] == L'\\' || path[0] == L'/' || path[1] == L':';
7306
7307}
7308
7309/* join root and rest with a backslash */
7310static void
7311_joinW(WCHAR *dest_path, const WCHAR *root, const WCHAR *rest)
7312{
7313 size_t root_len;
7314
7315 if (_is_absW(rest)) {
7316 wcscpy(dest_path, rest);
7317 return;
7318 }
7319
7320 root_len = wcslen(root);
7321
7322 wcscpy(dest_path, root);
7323 if(root_len) {
7324 dest_path[root_len] = L'\\';
7325 root_len++;
7326 }
7327 wcscpy(dest_path+root_len, rest);
7328}
7329
7330/* Return True if the path at src relative to dest is a directory */
7331static int
7332_check_dirW(LPCWSTR src, LPCWSTR dest)
7333{
7334 WIN32_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_DATA src_info;
7335 WCHAR dest_parent[MAX_PATH];
7336 WCHAR src_resolved[MAX_PATH] = L"";
7337
7338 /* dest_parent = os.path.dirname(dest) */
7339 wcscpy(dest_parent, dest);
7340 _dirnameW(dest_parent);
7341 /* src_resolved = os.path.join(dest_parent, src) */
7342 _joinW(src_resolved, dest_parent, src);
7343 return (
7344 GetFileAttributesExW(src_resolved, GetFileExInfoStandard, &src_info)
7345 && src_info.dwFileAttributes & FILE_ATTRIBUTE_DIRECTORY
7346 );
7347}
7348#endif

7351/*[clinic input]
7352os.symlink
7353 src: path_t
7354 dst: path_t
7355 target_is_directory: bool = False
7356 *
7357 dir_fd: dir_fd(requires='symlinkat')=None
7358
7359# "symlink(src, dst, target_is_directory=False, *, dir_fd=None)\n\n\
7360
7361Create a symbolic link pointing to src named dst.
7362
7363target_is_directory is required on Windows if the target is to be
7364 interpreted as a directory. (On Windows, symlink requires
7365 Windows 6.0 or greater, and raises a NotImplementedError otherwise.)
7366 target_is_directory is ignored on non-Windows platforms.
7367
7368If dir_fd is not None, it should be a file descriptor open to a directory,
7369 and path should be relative; path will then be relative to that directory.
7370dir_fd may not be implemented on your platform.
7371 If it is unavailable, using it will raise a NotImplementedError.
7372
7373[clinic start generated code]*/
7374
7375static PyObject *
7376os_symlink_impl(PyObject *module, path_t *src, path_t *dst,
7377 int target_is_directory, int dir_fd)
7378/*[clinic end generated code: output=08ca9f3f3cf960f6 input=e820ec4472547bc3]*/
7379{
7380#ifdef MS_WINDOWS
7381 DWORD result;
7382#else
7383 int result;
7384#endif
7385
7386#ifdef MS_WINDOWS
7387 if (!check_CreateSymbolicLink()) {
7388 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_NotImplementedError,
7389 "CreateSymbolicLink functions not found");
7390 return NULL;
7391 }
7392 if (!win32_can_symlink) {
7393 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_OSError, "symbolic link privilege not held");
7394 return NULL;
7395 }
7396#endif
7397
7398 if ((src->narrow && dst->wide) || (src->wide && dst->narrow)) {
7399 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError,
7400 "symlink: src and dst must be the same type");
7401 return NULL;
7402 }
7403
7404#ifdef MS_WINDOWS
7405
7406 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
7407 /* if src is a directory, ensure target_is_directory==1 */
7408 target_is_directory |= _check_dirW(src->wide, dst->wide);
7409 result = Py_CreateSymbolicLinkW(dst->wide, src->wide,
7410 target_is_directory);
7411 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
7412
7413 if (!result)
7414 return path_error2(src, dst);
7415
7416#else
7417
7418 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
7419#if HAVE_SYMLINKAT
7420 if (dir_fd != DEFAULT_DIR_FD)
7421 result = symlinkat(src->narrow, dir_fd, dst->narrow);
7422 else
7423#endif
7424 result = symlink(src->narrow, dst->narrow);
7425 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
7426
7427 if (result)
7428 return path_error2(src, dst);
7429#endif
7430
7431 Py_RETURN_NONE;
7432}
7433#endif /* HAVE_SYMLINK */

7438static PyStructSequence_Field times_result_fields[] = {
7439 {"user", "user time"},
7440 {"system", "system time"},
7441 {"children_user", "user time of children"},
7442 {"children_system", "system time of children"},
7443 {"elapsed", "elapsed time since an arbitrary point in the past"},
7444 {NULL}
7445};
7446
7447PyDoc_STRVAR(times_result__doc__,
7448"times_result: Result from os.times().\n\n\
7449This object may be accessed either as a tuple of\n\
7450 (user, system, children_user, children_system, elapsed),\n\
7451or via the attributes user, system, children_user, children_system,\n\
7452and elapsed.\n\
7453\n\
7454See os.times for more information.");
7455
7456static PyStructSequence_Desc times_result_desc = {
7457 "times_result", /* name */
7458 times_result__doc__, /* doc */
7459 times_result_fields,
7460 5
7461};
7462
7463static PyTypeObject TimesResultType;
7464
7465#ifdef MS_WINDOWS
7466#define HAVE_TIMES /* mandatory, for the method table */
7467#endif
7468
7469#ifdef HAVE_TIMES
7470
7471static PyObject *
7472build_times_result(double user, double system,
7473 double children_user, double children_system,
7474 double elapsed)
7475{
7476 PyObject *value = PyStructSequence_New(&TimesResultType);
7477 if (value == NULL)
7478 return NULL;
7479
7480#define SET(i, field) \
7481 { \
7482 PyObject *o = PyFloat_FromDouble(field); \
7483 if (!o) { \
7484 Py_DECREF(value); \
7485 return NULL; \
7486 } \
7487 PyStructSequence_SET_ITEM(value, i, o); \
7488 } \
7489
7490 SET(0, user);
7491 SET(1, system);
7492 SET(2, children_user);
7493 SET(3, children_system);
7494 SET(4, elapsed);
7495
7496#undef SET
7497
7498 return value;
7499}

7502#ifndef MS_WINDOWS
7503#define NEED_TICKS_PER_SECOND
7504static long ticks_per_second = -1;
7505#endif /* MS_WINDOWS */
7506
7507/*[clinic input]
7508os.times
7509
7510Return a collection containing process timing information.
7511
7512The object returned behaves like a named tuple with these fields:
7513 (utime, stime, cutime, cstime, elapsed_time)
7514All fields are floating point numbers.
7515[clinic start generated code]*/
7516
7517static PyObject *
7518os_times_impl(PyObject *module)
7519/*[clinic end generated code: output=35f640503557d32a input=2bf9df3d6ab2e48b]*/
7520#ifdef MS_WINDOWS
7521{
7522 FILETIME create, exit, kernel, user;
7523 HANDLE hProc;
7524 hProc = GetCurrentProcess();
7525 GetProcessTimes(hProc, &create, &exit, &kernel, &user);
7526 /* The fields of a FILETIME structure are the hi and lo part
7527 of a 64-bit value expressed in 100 nanosecond units.
7528 1e7 is one second in such units; 1e-7 the inverse.
7529 429.4967296 is 2**32 / 1e7 or 2**32 * 1e-7.
7530 */
7531 return build_times_result(
7532 (double)(user.dwHighDateTime*429.4967296 +
7533 user.dwLowDateTime*1e-7),
7534 (double)(kernel.dwHighDateTime*429.4967296 +
7535 kernel.dwLowDateTime*1e-7),
7536 (double)0,
7537 (double)0,
7538 (double)0);
7539}
7540#else /* MS_WINDOWS */
7541{
7542
7543
7544 struct tms t;
7545 clock_t c;
7546 errno = 0;
7547 c = times(&t);
7548 if (c == (clock_t) -1)
7549 return posix_error();
7550 return build_times_result(
7551 (double)t.tms_utime / ticks_per_second,
7552 (double)t.tms_stime / ticks_per_second,
7553 (double)t.tms_cutime / ticks_per_second,
7554 (double)t.tms_cstime / ticks_per_second,
7555 (double)c / ticks_per_second);
7556}
7557#endif /* MS_WINDOWS */
7558#endif /* HAVE_TIMES */

7667/* Functions acting on file descriptors */
7668
7669#ifdef O_CLOEXEC
7670extern int _Py_open_cloexec_works;
7671#endif
7672
7673
7674/*[clinic input]
7675os.open -> int
7676 path: path_t
7677 flags: int
7678 mode: int = 0o777
7679 *
7680 dir_fd: dir_fd(requires='openat') = None
7681
7682# "open(path, flags, mode=0o777, *, dir_fd=None)\n\n\
7683
7684Open a file for low level IO. Returns a file descriptor (integer).
7685
7686If dir_fd is not None, it should be a file descriptor open to a directory,
7687 and path should be relative; path will then be relative to that directory.
7688dir_fd may not be implemented on your platform.
7689 If it is unavailable, using it will raise a NotImplementedError.
7690[clinic start generated code]*/
7691
7692static int
7693os_open_impl(PyObject *module, path_t *path, int flags, int mode, int dir_fd)
7694/*[clinic end generated code: output=abc7227888c8bc73 input=ad8623b29acd2934]*/
7695{
7696 int fd;
7697 int async_err = 0;
7698
7699#ifdef O_CLOEXEC
7700 int *atomic_flag_works = &_Py_open_cloexec_works;
7701#elif !defined(MS_WINDOWS)
7702 int *atomic_flag_works = NULL;
7703#endif
7704
7705#ifdef MS_WINDOWS
7706 flags |= O_NOINHERIT;
7707#elif defined(O_CLOEXEC)
7708 flags |= O_CLOEXEC;
7709#endif
7710
7711 _Py_BEGIN_SUPPRESS_IPH
7712 do {
7713 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
7714#ifdef MS_WINDOWS
7715 fd = _wopen(path->wide, flags, mode);
7716#else
7717#ifdef HAVE_OPENAT
7718 if (dir_fd != DEFAULT_DIR_FD)
7719 fd = openat(dir_fd, path->narrow, flags, mode);
7720 else
7721#endif /* HAVE_OPENAT */
7722 fd = open(path->narrow, flags, mode);
7723#endif /* !MS_WINDOWS */
7724 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
7725 } while (fd < 0 && errno == EINTR && !(async_err = PyErr_CheckSignals()));
7726 _Py_END_SUPPRESS_IPH
7727
7728 if (fd < 0) {
7729 if (!async_err)
7730 PyErr_SetFromErrnoWithFilenameObject(PyExc_OSError, path->object);
7731 return -1;
7732 }
7733
7734#ifndef MS_WINDOWS
7735 if (_Py_set_inheritable(fd, 0, atomic_flag_works) < 0) {
7736 close(fd);
7737 return -1;
7738 }
7739#endif
7740
7741 return fd;
7742}

7745/*[clinic input]
7746os.close
7747
7748 fd: int
7749
7750Close a file descriptor.
7751[clinic start generated code]*/
7752
7753static PyObject *
7754os_close_impl(PyObject *module, int fd)
7755/*[clinic end generated code: output=2fe4e93602822c14 input=2bc42451ca5c3223]*/
7756{
7757 int res;
7758 /* We do not want to retry upon EINTR: see http://lwn.net/Articles/576478/
7759 * and http://linux.derkeiler.com/Mailing-Lists/Kernel/2005-09/3000.html
7760 * for more details.
7761 */
7762 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
7763 _Py_BEGIN_SUPPRESS_IPH
7764 res = close(fd);
7765 _Py_END_SUPPRESS_IPH
7766 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
7767 if (res < 0)
7768 return posix_error();
7769 Py_RETURN_NONE;
7770}

7815/*[clinic input]
7816os.dup2
7817 fd: int
7818 fd2: int
7819 inheritable: bool=True
7820
7821Duplicate file descriptor.
7822[clinic start generated code]*/
7823
7824static PyObject *
7825os_dup2_impl(PyObject *module, int fd, int fd2, int inheritable)
7826/*[clinic end generated code: output=db832a2d872ccc5f input=76e96f511be0352f]*/
7827{
7828 int res;
7829#if defined(HAVE_DUP3) && \
7830 !(defined(HAVE_FCNTL_H) && defined(F_DUP2FD_CLOEXEC))
7831 /* dup3() is available on Linux 2.6.27+ and glibc 2.9 */
7832 int dup3_works = -1;
7833#endif
7834
7835 if (fd < 0 || fd2 < 0)
7836 return posix_error();
7837
7838 /* dup2() can fail with EINTR if the target FD is already open, because it
7839 * then has to be closed. See os_close_impl() for why we don't handle EINTR
7840 * upon close(), and therefore below.
7841 */
7842#ifdef MS_WINDOWS
7843 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
7844 _Py_BEGIN_SUPPRESS_IPH
7845 res = dup2(fd, fd2);
7846 _Py_END_SUPPRESS_IPH
7847 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
7848 if (res < 0)
7849 return posix_error();
7850
7851 /* Character files like console cannot be make non-inheritable */
7852 if (!inheritable && _Py_set_inheritable(fd2, 0, NULL) < 0) {
7853 close(fd2);
7854 return NULL;
7855 }
7856
7857#elif defined(HAVE_FCNTL_H) && defined(F_DUP2FD_CLOEXEC)
7858 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
7859 if (!inheritable)
7860 res = fcntl(fd, F_DUP2FD_CLOEXEC, fd2);
7861 else
7862 res = dup2(fd, fd2);
7863 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
7864 if (res < 0)
7865 return posix_error();
7866
7867#else
7868
7869#ifdef HAVE_DUP3
7870 if (!inheritable && dup3_works != 0) {
7871 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
7872 res = dup3(fd, fd2, O_CLOEXEC);
7873 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
7874 if (res < 0) {
7875 if (dup3_works == -1)
7876 dup3_works = (errno != ENOSYS);
7877 if (dup3_works)
7878 return posix_error();
7879 }
7880 }
7881
7882 if (inheritable || dup3_works == 0)
7883 {
7884#endif
7885 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
7886 res = dup2(fd, fd2);
7887 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
7888 if (res < 0)
7889 return posix_error();
7890
7891 if (!inheritable && _Py_set_inheritable(fd2, 0, NULL) < 0) {
7892 close(fd2);
7893 return NULL;
7894 }
7895#ifdef HAVE_DUP3
7896 }
7897#endif
7898
7899#endif
7900
7901 Py_RETURN_NONE;
7902}

7907os.lockf

7910 An open file descriptor.

7939/*[clinic input]
7940os.lseek -> Py_off_t
7941
7942 fd: int
7943 position: Py_off_t
7944 how: int
7945 /
7946
7947Set the position of a file descriptor. Return the new position.
7948
7949Return the new cursor position in number of bytes
7950relative to the beginning of the file.
7951[clinic start generated code]*/
7952
7953static Py_off_t
7954os_lseek_impl(PyObject *module, int fd, Py_off_t position, int how)
7955/*[clinic end generated code: output=971e1efb6b30bd2f input=902654ad3f96a6d3]*/
7956{
7957 Py_off_t result;
7958
7959#ifdef SEEK_SET
7960 /* Turn 0, 1, 2 into SEEK_{SET,CUR,END} */
7961 switch (how) {
7962 case 0: how = SEEK_SET; break;
7963 case 1: how = SEEK_CUR; break;
7964 case 2: how = SEEK_END; break;
7965 }
7966#endif /* SEEK_END */
7967
7968 if (PyErr_Occurred())
7969 return -1;
7970
7971 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
7972 _Py_BEGIN_SUPPRESS_IPH
7973#ifdef MS_WINDOWS
7974 result = _lseeki64(fd, position, how);
7975#else
7976 result = lseek(fd, position, how);
7977#endif
7978 _Py_END_SUPPRESS_IPH
7979 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
7980 if (result < 0)
7981 posix_error();
7982
7983 return result;
7984}

7987/*[clinic input]
7988os.read
7989 fd: int
7990 length: Py_ssize_t
7991 /
7992
7993Read from a file descriptor. Returns a bytes object.
7994[clinic start generated code]*/
7995
7996static PyObject *
7997os_read_impl(PyObject *module, int fd, Py_ssize_t length)
7998/*[clinic end generated code: output=dafbe9a5cddb987b input=1df2eaa27c0bf1d3]*/
7999{
8000 Py_ssize_t n;
8001 PyObject *buffer;
8002
8003 if (length < 0) {
8004 errno = EINVAL;
8005 return posix_error();
8006 }
8007
8008#ifdef MS_WINDOWS
8009 /* On Windows, the count parameter of read() is an int */
8010 if (length > INT_MAX)
8011 length = INT_MAX;
8012#endif
8013
8014 buffer = PyBytes_FromStringAndSize((char *)NULL, length);
8015 if (buffer == NULL)
8016 return NULL;
8017
8018 n = _Py_read(fd, PyBytes_AS_STRING(buffer), length);
8019 if (n == -1) {
8020 Py_DECREF(buffer);
8021 return NULL;
8022 }
8023
8024 if (n != length)
8025 _PyBytes_Resize(&buffer, n);
8026
8027 return buffer;
8028}
8029
8030#if (defined(HAVE_SENDFILE) && (defined(__FreeBSD__) || defined(__DragonFly__) \
8031 || defined(__APPLE__))) || defined(HAVE_READV) || defined(HAVE_WRITEV)
8032static Py_ssize_t
8033iov_setup(struct iovec **iov, Py_buffer **buf, PyObject *seq, Py_ssize_t cnt, int type)
8034{
8035 Py_ssize_t i, j;
8036 Py_ssize_t blen, total = 0;
8037
8038 *iov = PyMem_New(struct iovec, cnt);
8039 if (*iov == NULL) {
8040 PyErr_NoMemory();
8041 return -1;
8042 }
8043
8044 *buf = PyMem_New(Py_buffer, cnt);
8045 if (*buf == NULL) {
8046 PyMem_Del(*iov);
8047 PyErr_NoMemory();
8048 return -1;
8049 }
8050
8051 for (i = 0; i < cnt; i++) {
8052 PyObject *item = PySequence_GetItem(seq, i);
8053 if (item == NULL)
8054 goto fail;
8055 if (PyObject_GetBuffer(item, &(*buf)[i], type) == -1) {
8056 Py_DECREF(item);
8057 goto fail;
8058 }
8059 Py_DECREF(item);
8060 (*iov)[i].iov_base = (*buf)[i].buf;
8061 blen = (*buf)[i].len;
8062 (*iov)[i].iov_len = blen;
8063 total += blen;
8064 }
8065 return total;
8066
8067fail:
8068 PyMem_Del(*iov);
8069 for (j = 0; j < i; j++) {
8070 PyBuffer_Release(&(*buf)[j]);
8071 }
8072 PyMem_Del(*buf);
8073 return -1;
8074}
8075
8076static void
8077iov_cleanup(struct iovec *iov, Py_buffer *buf, int cnt)
8078{
8079 int i;
8080 PyMem_Del(iov);
8081 for (i = 0; i < cnt; i++) {
8082 PyBuffer_Release(&buf[i]);
8083 }
8084 PyMem_Del(buf);
8085}
8086#endif

8089#ifdef HAVE_READV
8090/*[clinic input]
8091os.readv -> Py_ssize_t
8092
8093 fd: int
8094 buffers: object
8095 /
8096
8097Read from a file descriptor fd into an iterable of buffers.
8098
8099The buffers should be mutable buffers accepting bytes.
8100readv will transfer data into each buffer until it is full
8101and then move on to the next buffer in the sequence to hold
8102the rest of the data.
8103
8104readv returns the total number of bytes read,
8105which may be less than the total capacity of all the buffers.
8106[clinic start generated code]*/
8107
8108static Py_ssize_t
8109os_readv_impl(PyObject *module, int fd, PyObject *buffers)
8110/*[clinic end generated code: output=792da062d3fcebdb input=e679eb5dbfa0357d]*/
8111{
8112 Py_ssize_t cnt, n;
8113 int async_err = 0;
8114 struct iovec *iov;
8115 Py_buffer *buf;
8116
8117 if (!PySequence_Check(buffers)) {
8118 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
8119 "readv() arg 2 must be a sequence");
8120 return -1;
8121 }
8122
8123 cnt = PySequence_Size(buffers);
8124 if (cnt < 0)
8125 return -1;
8126
8127 if (iov_setup(&iov, &buf, buffers, cnt, PyBUF_WRITABLE) < 0)
8128 return -1;
8129
8130 do {
8131 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
8132 n = readv(fd, iov, cnt);
8133 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
8134 } while (n < 0 && errno == EINTR && !(async_err = PyErr_CheckSignals()));
8135
8136 iov_cleanup(iov, buf, cnt);
8137 if (n < 0) {
8138 if (!async_err)
8139 posix_error();
8140 return -1;
8141 }
8142
8143 return n;
8144}
8145#endif /* HAVE_READV */

8148#ifdef HAVE_PREAD
8149/*[clinic input]
8150# TODO length should be size_t! but Python doesn't support parsing size_t yet.
8151os.pread
8152
8153 fd: int
8154 length: int
8155 offset: Py_off_t
8156 /
8157
8158Read a number of bytes from a file descriptor starting at a particular offset.
8159
8160Read length bytes from file descriptor fd, starting at offset bytes from
8161the beginning of the file. The file offset remains unchanged.
8162[clinic start generated code]*/
8163
8164static PyObject *
8165os_pread_impl(PyObject *module, int fd, int length, Py_off_t offset)
8166/*[clinic end generated code: output=435b29ee32b54a78 input=084948dcbaa35d4c]*/
8167{

8170 PyObject *buffer;
8171
8172 if (length < 0) {
8173 errno = EINVAL;
8174 return posix_error();
8175 }
8176 buffer = PyBytes_FromStringAndSize((char *)NULL, length);
8177 if (buffer == NULL)
8178 return NULL;
8179
8180 do {
8181 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
8182 _Py_BEGIN_SUPPRESS_IPH
8183 n = pread(fd, PyBytes_AS_STRING(buffer), length, offset);
8184 _Py_END_SUPPRESS_IPH
8185 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
8186 } while (n < 0 && errno == EINTR && !(async_err = PyErr_CheckSignals()));
8187
8188 if (n < 0) {

8190 return (!async_err) ? posix_error() : NULL;

8216#ifdef HAVE_SENDFILE
8217PyDoc_STRVAR(posix_sendfile__doc__,
8218"sendfile(out, in, offset, count) -> byteswritten\n\
8219sendfile(out, in, offset, count[, headers][, trailers], flags=0)\n\
8220 -> byteswritten\n\
8221Copy count bytes from file descriptor in to file descriptor out.");
8222
8223/* AC 3.5: don't bother converting, has optional group*/
8224static PyObject *
8225posix_sendfile(PyObject *self, PyObject *args, PyObject *kwdict)
8226{
8227 int in, out;
8228 Py_ssize_t ret;
8229 int async_err = 0;
8230 off_t offset;
8231
8232#if defined(__FreeBSD__) || defined(__DragonFly__) || defined(__APPLE__)
8233#ifndef __APPLE__
8234 Py_ssize_t len;
8235#endif
8236 PyObject *headers = NULL, *trailers = NULL;
8237 Py_buffer *hbuf, *tbuf;
8238 off_t sbytes;
8239 struct sf_hdtr sf;
8240 int flags = 0;
8241 /* Beware that "in" clashes with Python's own "in" operator keyword */
8242 static char *keywords[] = {"out", "in",
8243 "offset", "count",
8244 "headers", "trailers", "flags", NULL};
8245
8246 sf.headers = NULL;
8247 sf.trailers = NULL;
8248
8249#ifdef __APPLE__
8250 if (!PyArg_ParseTupleAndKeywords(args, kwdict, "iiO&O&|OOi:sendfile",
8251 keywords, &out, &in, Py_off_t_converter, &offset, Py_off_t_converter, &sbytes,
8252#else
8253 if (!PyArg_ParseTupleAndKeywords(args, kwdict, "iiO&n|OOi:sendfile",
8254 keywords, &out, &in, Py_off_t_converter, &offset, &len,
8255#endif
8256 &headers, &trailers, &flags))
8257 return NULL;
8258 if (headers != NULL) {
8259 if (!PySequence_Check(headers)) {
8260 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
8261 "sendfile() headers must be a sequence");
8262 return NULL;
8263 } else {
8264 Py_ssize_t i = PySequence_Size(headers);
8265 if (i < 0)
8266 return NULL;
8267 if (i > INT_MAX) {
8268 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_OverflowError,
8269 "sendfile() header is too large");
8270 return NULL;
8271 }
8272 if (i > 0) {
8273 sf.hdr_cnt = (int)i;
8274 i = iov_setup(&(sf.headers), &hbuf,
8275 headers, sf.hdr_cnt, PyBUF_SIMPLE);
8276 if (i < 0)
8277 return NULL;
8278#ifdef __APPLE__
8279 sbytes += i;
8280#endif
8281 }
8282 }
8283 }
8284 if (trailers != NULL) {
8285 if (!PySequence_Check(trailers)) {
8286 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
8287 "sendfile() trailers must be a sequence");
8288 return NULL;
8289 } else {
8290 Py_ssize_t i = PySequence_Size(trailers);
8291 if (i < 0)
8292 return NULL;
8293 if (i > INT_MAX) {
8294 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_OverflowError,
8295 "sendfile() trailer is too large");
8296 return NULL;
8297 }
8298 if (i > 0) {
8299 sf.trl_cnt = (int)i;
8300 i = iov_setup(&(sf.trailers), &tbuf,
8301 trailers, sf.trl_cnt, PyBUF_SIMPLE);
8302 if (i < 0)
8303 return NULL;
8304#ifdef __APPLE__
8305 sbytes += i;
8306#endif
8307 }
8308 }
8309 }
8310
8311 _Py_BEGIN_SUPPRESS_IPH
8312 do {
8313 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
8314#ifdef __APPLE__
8315 ret = sendfile(in, out, offset, &sbytes, &sf, flags);
8316#else
8317 ret = sendfile(in, out, offset, len, &sf, &sbytes, flags);
8318#endif
8319 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
8320 } while (ret < 0 && errno == EINTR && !(async_err = PyErr_CheckSignals()));
8321 _Py_END_SUPPRESS_IPH
8322
8323 if (sf.headers != NULL)
8324 iov_cleanup(sf.headers, hbuf, sf.hdr_cnt);
8325 if (sf.trailers != NULL)
8326 iov_cleanup(sf.trailers, tbuf, sf.trl_cnt);
8327
8328 if (ret < 0) {
8329 if ((errno == EAGAIN) || (errno == EBUSY)) {
8330 if (sbytes != 0) {
8331 // some data has been sent
8332 goto done;
8333 }
8334 else {
8335 // no data has been sent; upper application is supposed
8336 // to retry on EAGAIN or EBUSY
8337 return posix_error();
8338 }
8339 }
8340 return (!async_err) ? posix_error() : NULL;
8341 }
8342 goto done;
8343
8344done:
8345 #if !defined(HAVE_LARGEFILE_SUPPORT)
8346 return Py_BuildValue("l", sbytes);
8347 #else
8348 return Py_BuildValue("L", sbytes);
8349 #endif
8350
8351#else
8352 Py_ssize_t count;
8353 PyObject *offobj;
8354 static char *keywords[] = {"out", "in",
8355 "offset", "count", NULL};
8356 if (!PyArg_ParseTupleAndKeywords(args, kwdict, "iiOn:sendfile",
8357 keywords, &out, &in, &offobj, &count))
8358 return NULL;
8359#ifdef __linux__
8360 if (offobj == Py_None) {
8361 do {
8362 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
8363 ret = sendfile(out, in, NULL, count);
8364 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
8365 } while (ret < 0 && errno == EINTR && !(async_err = PyErr_CheckSignals()));
8366 if (ret < 0)
8367 return (!async_err) ? posix_error() : NULL;
8368 return Py_BuildValue("n", ret);
8369 }
8370#endif
8371 if (!Py_off_t_converter(offobj, &offset))
8372 return NULL;
8373
8374 do {
8375 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
8376 ret = sendfile(out, in, &offset, count);
8377 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
8378 } while (ret < 0 && errno == EINTR && !(async_err = PyErr_CheckSignals()));
8379 if (ret < 0)
8380 return (!async_err) ? posix_error() : NULL;
8381 return Py_BuildValue("n", ret);
8382#endif
8383}
8384#endif /* HAVE_SENDFILE */

8446#ifdef HAVE_PIPE
8447/*[clinic input]
8448os.pipe
8449
8450Create a pipe.
8451
8452Returns a tuple of two file descriptors:
8453 (read_fd, write_fd)
8454[clinic start generated code]*/
8455
8456static PyObject *
8457os_pipe_impl(PyObject *module)
8458/*[clinic end generated code: output=ff9b76255793b440 input=02535e8c8fa6c4d4]*/
8459{
8460 int fds[2];
8461#ifdef MS_WINDOWS
8462 HANDLE read, write;
8463 SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES attr;
8464 BOOL ok;
8465#else
8466 int res;
8467#endif
8468
8469#ifdef MS_WINDOWS
8470 attr.nLength = sizeof(attr);
8471 attr.lpSecurityDescriptor = NULL;
8472 attr.bInheritHandle = FALSE;
8473
8474 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
8475 _Py_BEGIN_SUPPRESS_IPH
8476 ok = CreatePipe(&read, &write, &attr, 0);
8477 if (ok) {
8478 fds[0] = _open_osfhandle((intptr_t)read, _O_RDONLY);
8479 fds[1] = _open_osfhandle((intptr_t)write, _O_WRONLY);
8480 if (fds[0] == -1 || fds[1] == -1) {
8481 CloseHandle(read);
8482 CloseHandle(write);
8483 ok = 0;
8484 }
8485 }
8486 _Py_END_SUPPRESS_IPH
8487 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
8488
8489 if (!ok)
8490 return PyErr_SetFromWindowsErr(0);
8491#else
8492
8493#ifdef HAVE_PIPE2
8494 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
8495 res = pipe2(fds, O_CLOEXEC);
8496 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
8497
8498 if (res != 0 && errno == ENOSYS)
8499 {
8500#endif
8501 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
8502 res = pipe(fds);
8503 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
8504
8505 if (res == 0) {
8506 if (_Py_set_inheritable(fds[0], 0, NULL) < 0) {
8507 close(fds[0]);
8508 close(fds[1]);
8509 return NULL;
8510 }
8511 if (_Py_set_inheritable(fds[1], 0, NULL) < 0) {
8512 close(fds[0]);
8513 close(fds[1]);
8514 return NULL;
8515 }
8516 }
8517#ifdef HAVE_PIPE2
8518 }
8519#endif
8520
8521 if (res != 0)
8522 return PyErr_SetFromErrno(PyExc_OSError);
8523#endif /* !MS_WINDOWS */
8524 return Py_BuildValue("(ii)", fds[0], fds[1]);
8525}
8526#endif /* HAVE_PIPE */

8649#ifdef HAVE_MKFIFO
8650/*[clinic input]
8651os.mkfifo
8652
8653 path: path_t
8654 mode: int=0o666
8655 *
8656 dir_fd: dir_fd(requires='mkfifoat')=None
8657
8658Create a "fifo" (a POSIX named pipe).
8659
8660If dir_fd is not None, it should be a file descriptor open to a directory,
8661 and path should be relative; path will then be relative to that directory.
8662dir_fd may not be implemented on your platform.
8663 If it is unavailable, using it will raise a NotImplementedError.
8664[clinic start generated code]*/
8665
8666static PyObject *
8667os_mkfifo_impl(PyObject *module, path_t *path, int mode, int dir_fd)
8668/*[clinic end generated code: output=ce41cfad0e68c940 input=73032e98a36e0e19]*/
8669{
8670 int result;
8671 int async_err = 0;
8672
8673 do {
8674 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
8675#ifdef HAVE_MKFIFOAT
8676 if (dir_fd != DEFAULT_DIR_FD)
8677 result = mkfifoat(dir_fd, path->narrow, mode);
8678 else
8679#endif
8680 result = mkfifo(path->narrow, mode);
8681 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
8682 } while (result != 0 && errno == EINTR &&
8683 !(async_err = PyErr_CheckSignals()));

8694os.mknod
8695
8696 path: path_t
8697 mode: int=0o600
8698 device: dev_t=0
8699 *
8700 dir_fd: dir_fd(requires='mknodat')=None
8701
8702Create a node in the file system.
8703
8704Create a node in the file system (file, device special file or named pipe)
8705at path. mode specifies both the permissions to use and the
8706type of node to be created, being combined (bitwise OR) with one of
8707S_IFREG, S_IFCHR, S_IFBLK, and S_IFIFO. If S_IFCHR or S_IFBLK is set on mode,
8708device defines the newly created device special file (probably using
8709os.makedev()). Otherwise device is ignored.
8710
8711If dir_fd is not None, it should be a file descriptor open to a directory,
8712 and path should be relative; path will then be relative to that directory.
8713dir_fd may not be implemented on your platform.

8715[clinic start generated code]*/

8836/*[clinic input]
8837os.truncate
8838 path: path_t(allow_fd='PATH_HAVE_FTRUNCATE')
8839 length: Py_off_t
8840
8841Truncate a file, specified by path, to a specific length.
8842
8843On some platforms, path may also be specified as an open file descriptor.
8844 If this functionality is unavailable, using it raises an exception.
8845[clinic start generated code]*/
8846
8847static PyObject *
8848os_truncate_impl(PyObject *module, path_t *path, Py_off_t length)
8849/*[clinic end generated code: output=43009c8df5c0a12b input=77229cf0b50a9b77]*/
8850{
8851 int result;
8852#ifdef MS_WINDOWS
8853 int fd;
8854#endif
8855
8856 if (path->fd != -1)
8857 return os_ftruncate_impl(module, path->fd, length);
8858
8859 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
8860 _Py_BEGIN_SUPPRESS_IPH
8861#ifdef MS_WINDOWS
8862 fd = _wopen(path->wide, _O_WRONLY | _O_BINARY | _O_NOINHERIT);
8863 if (fd < 0)
8864 result = -1;
8865 else {
8866 result = _chsize_s(fd, length);
8867 close(fd);
8868 if (result < 0)
8869 errno = result;
8870 }
8871#else
8872 result = truncate(path->narrow, length);
8873#endif
8874 _Py_END_SUPPRESS_IPH
8875 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
8876 if (result < 0)
8877 return path_error(path);
8878
8879 Py_RETURN_NONE;

8980#ifdef HAVE_PUTENV
8981
8982/* Save putenv() parameters as values here, so we can collect them when they
8983 * get re-set with another call for the same key. */
8984static PyObject *posix_putenv_garbage;
8985
8986static void
8987posix_putenv_garbage_setitem(PyObject *name, PyObject *value)
8988{
8989 /* Install the first arg and newstr in posix_putenv_garbage;
8990 * this will cause previous value to be collected. This has to
8991 * happen after the real putenv() call because the old value
8992 * was still accessible until then. */
8993 if (PyDict_SetItem(posix_putenv_garbage, name, value))
8994 /* really not much we can do; just leak */
8995 PyErr_Clear();
8996 else
8997 Py_DECREF(value);
8998}
8999
9000
9001#ifdef MS_WINDOWS
9002/*[clinic input]
9003os.putenv
9004
9005 name: unicode
9006 value: unicode
9007 /
9008
9009Change or add an environment variable.
9010[clinic start generated code]*/
9011
9012static PyObject *
9013os_putenv_impl(PyObject *module, PyObject *name, PyObject *value)
9014/*[clinic end generated code: output=d29a567d6b2327d2 input=ba586581c2e6105f]*/
9015{
9016 const wchar_t *env;
9017 Py_ssize_t size;
9018
9019 /* Search from index 1 because on Windows starting '=' is allowed for
9020 defining hidden environment variables. */
9021 if (PyUnicode_GET_LENGTH(name) == 0 ||
9022 PyUnicode_FindChar(name, '=', 1, PyUnicode_GET_LENGTH(name), 1) != -1)
9023 {
9024 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError, "illegal environment variable name");
9025 return NULL;
9026 }
9027 PyObject *unicode = PyUnicode_FromFormat("%U=%U", name, value);
9028 if (unicode == NULL) {
9029 return NULL;
9030 }
9031
9032 env = PyUnicode_AsUnicodeAndSize(unicode, &size);
9033 if (env == NULL)
9034 goto error;
9035 if (size > _MAX_ENV) {
9036 PyErr_Format(PyExc_ValueError,
9037 "the environment variable is longer than %u characters",
9038 _MAX_ENV);
9039 goto error;
9040 }
9041 if (wcslen(env) != (size_t)size) {
9042 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError, "embedded null character");
9043 goto error;
9044 }
9045
9046 if (_wputenv(env)) {
9047 posix_error();
9048 goto error;
9049 }
9050
9051 posix_putenv_garbage_setitem(name, unicode);
9052 Py_RETURN_NONE;
9053
9054error:
9055 Py_DECREF(unicode);
9056 return NULL;
9057}
9058#else /* MS_WINDOWS */
9059/*[clinic input]
9060os.putenv
9061
9062 name: FSConverter
9063 value: FSConverter
9064 /
9065
9066Change or add an environment variable.
9067[clinic start generated code]*/
9068
9069static PyObject *
9070os_putenv_impl(PyObject *module, PyObject *name, PyObject *value)
9071/*[clinic end generated code: output=d29a567d6b2327d2 input=a97bc6152f688d31]*/
9072{
9073 PyObject *bytes = NULL;
9074 char *env;
9075 const char *name_string = PyBytes_AS_STRING(name);
9076 const char *value_string = PyBytes_AS_STRING(value);
9077
9078 if (strchr(name_string, '=') != NULL) {
9079 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError, "illegal environment variable name");
9080 return NULL;
9081 }
9082 bytes = PyBytes_FromFormat("%s=%s", name_string, value_string);
9083 if (bytes == NULL) {
9084 return NULL;
9085 }
9086
9087 env = PyBytes_AS_STRING(bytes);
9088 if (putenv(env)) {
9089 Py_DECREF(bytes);
9090 return posix_error();
9091 }
9092
9093 posix_putenv_garbage_setitem(name, bytes);
9094 Py_RETURN_NONE;
9095}
9096#endif /* MS_WINDOWS */
9097#endif /* HAVE_PUTENV */

9100#ifdef HAVE_UNSETENV
9101/*[clinic input]
9102os.unsetenv
9103 name: FSConverter
9104 /
9105
9106Delete an environment variable.
9107[clinic start generated code]*/
9108
9109static PyObject *
9110os_unsetenv_impl(PyObject *module, PyObject *name)
9111/*[clinic end generated code: output=54c4137ab1834f02 input=2bb5288a599c7107]*/
9112{
9113#ifndef HAVE_BROKEN_UNSETENV
9114 int err;
9115#endif
9116
9117#ifdef HAVE_BROKEN_UNSETENV
9118 unsetenv(PyBytes_AS_STRING(name));
9119#else
9120 err = unsetenv(PyBytes_AS_STRING(name));
9121 if (err)
9122 return posix_error();
9123#endif
9124
9125 /* Remove the key from posix_putenv_garbage;
9126 * this will cause it to be collected. This has to
9127 * happen after the real unsetenv() call because the
9128 * old value was still accessible until then.
9129 */
9130 if (PyDict_DelItem(posix_putenv_garbage, name)) {
9131 /* really not much we can do; just leak */
9132 PyErr_Clear();
9133 }
9134 Py_RETURN_NONE;
9135}
9136#endif /* HAVE_UNSETENV */

9140os.strerror
9141
9142 code: int
9143 /
9144
9145Translate an error code to a message string.
9146[clinic start generated code]*/
9147
9148static PyObject *
9149os_strerror_impl(PyObject *module, int code)
9150/*[clinic end generated code: output=baebf09fa02a78f2 input=75a8673d97915a91]*/
