9327
9328#if defined(HAVE_FSTATVFS) && defined(HAVE_SYS_STATVFS_H)
9329#ifdef _SCO_DS
9330/* SCO OpenServer 5.0 and later requires _SVID3 before it reveals the
9331 needed definitions in sys/statvfs.h */
9332#define _SVID3
9333#endif
9334#include <sys/statvfs.h>
9335
9336static PyObject*
9337_pystatvfs_fromstructstatvfs(struct statvfs st) {
9338 PyObject *v = PyStructSequence_New(&StatVFSResultType);
9339 if (v == NULL)
9340 return NULL;
9341
9342#if !defined(HAVE_LARGEFILE_SUPPORT)
9343 PyStructSequence_SET_ITEM(v, 0, PyLong_FromLong((long) st.f_bsize));
9344 PyStructSequence_SET_ITEM(v, 1, PyLong_FromLong((long) st.f_frsize));
9345 PyStructSequence_SET_ITEM(v, 2, PyLong_FromLong((long) st.f_blocks));
9346 PyStructSequence_SET_ITEM(v, 3, PyLong_FromLong((long) st.f_bfree));
9347 PyStructSequence_SET_ITEM(v, 4, PyLong_FromLong((long) st.f_bavail));
9348 PyStructSequence_SET_ITEM(v, 5, PyLong_FromLong((long) st.f_files));
9349 PyStructSequence_SET_ITEM(v, 6, PyLong_FromLong((long) st.f_ffree));
9350 PyStructSequence_SET_ITEM(v, 7, PyLong_FromLong((long) st.f_favail));
9351 PyStructSequence_SET_ITEM(v, 8, PyLong_FromLong((long) st.f_flag));
9352 PyStructSequence_SET_ITEM(v, 9, PyLong_FromLong((long) st.f_namemax));
9353#else
9354 PyStructSequence_SET_ITEM(v, 0, PyLong_FromLong((long) st.f_bsize));
9355 PyStructSequence_SET_ITEM(v, 1, PyLong_FromLong((long) st.f_frsize));
9356 PyStructSequence_SET_ITEM(v, 2,
9357 PyLong_FromLongLong((long long) st.f_blocks));
9358 PyStructSequence_SET_ITEM(v, 3,
9359 PyLong_FromLongLong((long long) st.f_bfree));
9360 PyStructSequence_SET_ITEM(v, 4,
9361 PyLong_FromLongLong((long long) st.f_bavail));
9362 PyStructSequence_SET_ITEM(v, 5,
9363 PyLong_FromLongLong((long long) st.f_files));
9364 PyStructSequence_SET_ITEM(v, 6,
9365 PyLong_FromLongLong((long long) st.f_ffree));
9366 PyStructSequence_SET_ITEM(v, 7,
9367 PyLong_FromLongLong((long long) st.f_favail));
9368 PyStructSequence_SET_ITEM(v, 8, PyLong_FromLong((long) st.f_flag));
9369 PyStructSequence_SET_ITEM(v, 9, PyLong_FromLong((long) st.f_namemax));
9370#endif
9371 if (PyErr_Occurred()) {
9372 Py_DECREF(v);
9373 return NULL;
9374 }
9375
9376 return v;
9377}

9380/*[clinic input]
9381os.fstatvfs
9382 fd: int
9383 /
9384
9385Perform an fstatvfs system call on the given fd.
9386
9387Equivalent to statvfs(fd).
9388[clinic start generated code]*/
9389
9390static PyObject *
9391os_fstatvfs_impl(PyObject *module, int fd)
9392/*[clinic end generated code: output=53547cf0cc55e6c5 input=d8122243ac50975e]*/
9393{
9394 int result;
9395 int async_err = 0;
9396 struct statvfs st;
9397
9398 do {
9399 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
9400 result = fstatvfs(fd, &st);
9401 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
9402 } while (result != 0 && errno == EINTR &&
9403 !(async_err = PyErr_CheckSignals()));
9404 if (result != 0)
9405 return (!async_err) ? posix_error() : NULL;
9406
9407 return _pystatvfs_fromstructstatvfs(st);
9408}
9409#endif /* defined(HAVE_FSTATVFS) && defined(HAVE_SYS_STATVFS_H) */

9414/*[clinic input]
9415os.statvfs

9423 If this functionality is unavailable, using it raises an exception.
9424[clinic start generated code]*/

9426static PyObject *
9427os_statvfs_impl(PyObject *module, path_t *path)
9428/*[clinic end generated code: output=87106dd1beb8556e input=3f5c35791c669bd9]*/
9429{
9430 int result;
9431 struct statvfs st;
9432
9433 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS

9436#ifdef __APPLE__

9438 if (fstatvfs == NULL) {
9439 fd_specified("statvfs", path->fd);
9440 return NULL;
9441 }
9442#endif
9443 result = fstatvfs(path->fd, &st);

9445 else

9467

9471{

9477 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS

9480

9486/* This is used for fpathconf(), pathconf(), confstr() and sysconf().
9487 * It maps strings representing configuration variable names to
9488 * integer values, allowing those functions to be called with the
9489 * magic names instead of polluting the module's namespace with tons of
9490 * rarely-used constants. There are three separate tables that use
9491 * these definitions.
9492 *
9493 * This code is always included, even if none of the interfaces that
9494 * need it are included. The #if hackery needed to avoid it would be
9495 * sufficiently pervasive that it's not worth the loss of readability.
9496 */
9497struct constdef {
9498 const char *name;
9499 int value;
9500};
9501
9502static int
9503conv_confname(PyObject *arg, int *valuep, struct constdef *table,
9504 size_t tablesize)
9505{
9506 if (PyLong_Check(arg)) {
9507 int value = _PyLong_AsInt(arg);
9508 if (value == -1 && PyErr_Occurred())
9509 return 0;
9510 *valuep = value;
9511 return 1;
9512 }
9513 else {
9514 /* look up the value in the table using a binary search */
9515 size_t lo = 0;
9516 size_t mid;
9517 size_t hi = tablesize;
9518 int cmp;
9519 const char *confname;
9520 if (!PyUnicode_Check(arg)) {
9521 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
9522 "configuration names must be strings or integers");
9523 return 0;
9524 }
9525 confname = PyUnicode_AsUTF8(arg);
9526 if (confname == NULL)
9527 return 0;
9528 while (lo < hi) {
9529 mid = (lo + hi) / 2;
9530 cmp = strcmp(confname, table[mid].name);
9531 if (cmp < 0)
9532 hi = mid;
9533 else if (cmp > 0)
9534 lo = mid + 1;
9535 else {
9536 *valuep = table[mid].value;
9537 return 1;
9538 }
9539 }
9540 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError, "unrecognized configuration name");
9541 return 0;
9542 }
9543}

9680

9687os_pathconf_impl(PyObject *module, path_t *path, int name)
9688/*[clinic end generated code: output=5bedee35b293a089 input=bc3e2a985af27e5e]*/

9690 long limit;
9691
9692 errno = 0;
9693#ifdef HAVE_FPATHCONF
9694 if (path->fd != -1)
9695 limit = fpathconf(path->fd, name);
9696 else
9697#endif

9702 posix_error();
9703 else
9704 path_error(path);
9705 }
9706
9707 return limit;
9708}

9874/*[clinic input]
9875os.confstr
9876
9877 name: confstr_confname
9878 /
9879
9880Return a string-valued system configuration variable.
9881[clinic start generated code]*/
9882
9883static PyObject *
9884os_confstr_impl(PyObject *module, int name)
9885/*[clinic end generated code: output=bfb0b1b1e49b9383 input=18fb4d0567242e65]*/
9886{
9887 PyObject *result = NULL;
9888 char buffer[255];
9889 size_t len;
9890
9891 errno = 0;
9892 len = confstr(name, buffer, sizeof(buffer));
9893 if (len == 0) {
9894 if (errno) {
9895 posix_error();
9896 return NULL;
9897 }
9898 else {
9899 Py_RETURN_NONE;
9900 }
9901 }
9902
9903 if (len >= sizeof(buffer)) {
9904 size_t len2;
9905 char *buf = PyMem_Malloc(len);
9906 if (buf == NULL)
9907 return PyErr_NoMemory();
9908 len2 = confstr(name, buf, len);
9909 assert(len == len2);
9910 result = PyUnicode_DecodeFSDefaultAndSize(buf, len2-1);
9911 PyMem_Free(buf);
9912 }
9913 else
9914 result = PyUnicode_DecodeFSDefaultAndSize(buffer, len-1);
9915 return result;
9916}
9917#endif /* HAVE_CONFSTR */

10416static int
10417conv_sysconf_confname(PyObject *arg, int *valuep)
10418{
10419 return conv_confname(arg, valuep, posix_constants_sysconf,
10420 sizeof(posix_constants_sysconf)
10421 / sizeof(struct constdef));
10422}

10425/*[clinic input]
10426os.sysconf -> long
10427 name: sysconf_confname
10428 /
10429
10430Return an integer-valued system configuration variable.
10431[clinic start generated code]*/
10432
10433static long
10434os_sysconf_impl(PyObject *module, int name)
10435/*[clinic end generated code: output=3662f945fc0cc756 input=279e3430a33f29e4]*/
10436{
10437 long value;
10438
10439 errno = 0;
10440 value = sysconf(name);
10441 if (value == -1 && errno != 0)
10442 posix_error();
10443 return value;
10444}
10445#endif /* HAVE_SYSCONF */
10446
10447
10448/* This code is used to ensure that the tables of configuration value names
10449 * are in sorted order as required by conv_confname(), and also to build
10450 * the exported dictionaries that are used to publish information about the
10451 * names available on the host platform.
10452 *
10453 * Sorting the table at runtime ensures that the table is properly ordered
10454 * when used, even for platforms we're not able to test on. It also makes
10455 * it easier to add additional entries to the tables.
10456 */
10457
10458static int
10459cmp_constdefs(const void *v1, const void *v2)
10460{
10461 const struct constdef *c1 =
10462 (const struct constdef *) v1;
10463 const struct constdef *c2 =
10464 (const struct constdef *) v2;
10465
10466 return strcmp(c1->name, c2->name);
10467}
10468
10469static int
10470setup_confname_table(struct constdef *table, size_t tablesize,
10471 const char *tablename, PyObject *module)
10472{
10473 PyObject *d = NULL;
10474 size_t i;
10475
10476 qsort(table, tablesize, sizeof(struct constdef), cmp_constdefs);
10477 d = PyDict_New();
10478 if (d == NULL)
10479 return -1;
10480
10481 for (i=0; i < tablesize; ++i) {
10482 PyObject *o = PyLong_FromLong(table[i].value);
10483 if (o == NULL || PyDict_SetItemString(d, table[i].name, o) == -1) {
10484 Py_XDECREF(o);
10485 Py_DECREF(d);
10486 return -1;
10487 }
10488 Py_DECREF(o);
10489 }
10490 return PyModule_AddObject(module, tablename, d);
10491}
10492
10493/* Return -1 on failure, 0 on success. */
10494static int
10495setup_confname_tables(PyObject *module)
10496{
10497#if defined(HAVE_FPATHCONF) || defined(HAVE_PATHCONF)
10498 if (setup_confname_table(posix_constants_pathconf,
10499 sizeof(posix_constants_pathconf)
10500 / sizeof(struct constdef),
10501 "pathconf_names", module))
10502 return -1;
10503#endif
10504#ifdef HAVE_CONFSTR
10505 if (setup_confname_table(posix_constants_confstr,
10506 sizeof(posix_constants_confstr)
10507 / sizeof(struct constdef),
10508 "confstr_names", module))
10509 return -1;
10510#endif
10511#ifdef HAVE_SYSCONF
10512 if (setup_confname_table(posix_constants_sysconf,
10513 sizeof(posix_constants_sysconf)
10514 / sizeof(struct constdef),
10515 "sysconf_names", module))
10516 return -1;
10517#endif
10518 return 0;
10519}

10522/*[clinic input]
10523os.abort
10524
10525Abort the interpreter immediately.
10526
10527This function 'dumps core' or otherwise fails in the hardest way possible
10528on the hosting operating system. This function never returns.
10529[clinic start generated code]*/
10530
10531static PyObject *
10532os_abort_impl(PyObject *module)
10533/*[clinic end generated code: output=dcf52586dad2467c input=cf2c7d98bc504047]*/
10534{
10535 abort();
10536 /*NOTREACHED*/
10537#ifndef __clang__
10538 /* Issue #28152: abort() is declared with __attribute__((__noreturn__)).
10539 GCC emits a warning without "return NULL;" (compiler bug?), but Clang
10540 is smarter and emits a warning on the return. */
10541 Py_FatalError("abort() called from Python code didn't abort!");
10542 return NULL;
10543#endif
10544}
10545
10546#ifdef MS_WINDOWS
10547/* Grab ShellExecute dynamically from shell32 */
10548static int has_ShellExecute = -1;
10549static HINSTANCE (CALLBACK *Py_ShellExecuteW)(HWND, LPCWSTR, LPCWSTR, LPCWSTR,
10550 LPCWSTR, INT);
10551static int
10552check_ShellExecute()
10553{
10554 HINSTANCE hShell32;
10555
10556 /* only recheck */
10557 if (-1 == has_ShellExecute) {
10558 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
10559 hShell32 = LoadLibraryW(L"SHELL32");
10560 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
10561 if (hShell32) {
10562 *(FARPROC*)&Py_ShellExecuteW = GetProcAddress(hShell32,
10563 "ShellExecuteW");
10564 has_ShellExecute = Py_ShellExecuteW != NULL;
10565 } else {
10566 has_ShellExecute = 0;
10567 }
10568 }
10569 return has_ShellExecute;
10570}
10571
10572
10573/*[clinic input]
10574os.startfile
10575 filepath: path_t
10576 operation: Py_UNICODE = NULL
10577
10578startfile(filepath [, operation])
10579
10580Start a file with its associated application.
10581
10582When "operation" is not specified or "open", this acts like
10583double-clicking the file in Explorer, or giving the file name as an
10584argument to the DOS "start" command: the file is opened with whatever
10585application (if any) its extension is associated.
10586When another "operation" is given, it specifies what should be done with
10587the file. A typical operation is "print".
10588
10589startfile returns as soon as the associated application is launched.
10590There is no option to wait for the application to close, and no way
10591to retrieve the application's exit status.
10592
10593The filepath is relative to the current directory. If you want to use
10594an absolute path, make sure the first character is not a slash ("/");
10595the underlying Win32 ShellExecute function doesn't work if it is.
10596[clinic start generated code]*/
10597
10598static PyObject *
10599os_startfile_impl(PyObject *module, path_t *filepath, Py_UNICODE *operation)
10600/*[clinic end generated code: output=912ceba79acfa1c9 input=63950bf2986380d0]*/
10601{
10602 HINSTANCE rc;
10603
10604 if(!check_ShellExecute()) {
10605 /* If the OS doesn't have ShellExecute, return a
10606 NotImplementedError. */
10607 return PyErr_Format(PyExc_NotImplementedError,
10608 "startfile not available on this platform");
10609 }
10610
10611 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
10612 rc = Py_ShellExecuteW((HWND)0, operation, filepath->wide,
10613 NULL, NULL, SW_SHOWNORMAL);
10614 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
10615
10616 if (rc <= (HINSTANCE)32) {
10617 win32_error_object("startfile", filepath->object);
10618 return NULL;
10619 }
10620 Py_RETURN_NONE;
10621}

10756#ifdef USE_XATTRS
10757/*[clinic input]
10758os.getxattr
10759
10760 path: path_t(allow_fd=True)
10761 attribute: path_t
10762 *
10763 follow_symlinks: bool = True
10764
10765Return the value of extended attribute attribute on path.
10766
10767path may be either a string or an open file descriptor.
10768If follow_symlinks is False, and the last element of the path is a symbolic
10769 link, getxattr will examine the symbolic link itself instead of the file
10770 the link points to.
10771
10772[clinic start generated code]*/
10773
10774static PyObject *
10775os_getxattr_impl(PyObject *module, path_t *path, path_t *attribute,
10776 int follow_symlinks)
10777/*[clinic end generated code: output=5f2f44200a43cff2 input=8c8ea3bab78d89c2]*/
10778{
10779 Py_ssize_t i;
10780 PyObject *buffer = NULL;
10781
10782 if (fd_and_follow_symlinks_invalid("getxattr", path->fd, follow_symlinks))
10783 return NULL;
10784
10785 for (i = 0; ; i++) {
10786 void *ptr;
10787 ssize_t result;
10788 static const Py_ssize_t buffer_sizes[] = {128, XATTR_SIZE_MAX, 0};
10789 Py_ssize_t buffer_size = buffer_sizes[i];
10790 if (!buffer_size) {
10791 path_error(path);
10792 return NULL;
10793 }
10794 buffer = PyBytes_FromStringAndSize(NULL, buffer_size);
10795 if (!buffer)
10796 return NULL;
10797 ptr = PyBytes_AS_STRING(buffer);
10798
10799 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS;
10800 if (path->fd >= 0)
10801 result = fgetxattr(path->fd, attribute->narrow, ptr, buffer_size);
10802 else if (follow_symlinks)
10803 result = getxattr(path->narrow, attribute->narrow, ptr, buffer_size);
10804 else
10805 result = lgetxattr(path->narrow, attribute->narrow, ptr, buffer_size);
10806 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS;
10807
10808 if (result < 0) {
10809 Py_DECREF(buffer);
10810 if (errno == ERANGE)
10811 continue;
10812 path_error(path);
10813 return NULL;
10814 }
10815
10816 if (result != buffer_size) {
10817 /* Can only shrink. */
10818 _PyBytes_Resize(&buffer, result);
10819 }
10820 break;
10821 }
10822
10823 return buffer;
10824}

10834 *

10921/*[clinic input]
10922os.listxattr
10923
10924 path: path_t(allow_fd=True, nullable=True) = None
10925 *
10926 follow_symlinks: bool = True
10927
10928Return a list of extended attributes on path.
10929
10930path may be either None, a string, or an open file descriptor.
10931if path is None, listxattr will examine the current directory.
10932If follow_symlinks is False, and the last element of the path is a symbolic
10933 link, listxattr will examine the symbolic link itself instead of the file
10934 the link points to.
10935[clinic start generated code]*/
10936
10937static PyObject *
10938os_listxattr_impl(PyObject *module, path_t *path, int follow_symlinks)
10939/*[clinic end generated code: output=bebdb4e2ad0ce435 input=08cca53ac0b07c13]*/
10940{
10941 Py_ssize_t i;
10942 PyObject *result = NULL;
10943 const char *name;
10944 char *buffer = NULL;
10945
10946 if (fd_and_follow_symlinks_invalid("listxattr", path->fd, follow_symlinks))
10947 goto exit;
10948
10949 name = path->narrow ? path->narrow : ".";
10950
10951 for (i = 0; ; i++) {
10952 const char *start, *trace, *end;
10953 ssize_t length;
10954 static const Py_ssize_t buffer_sizes[] = { 256, XATTR_LIST_MAX, 0 };
10955 Py_ssize_t buffer_size = buffer_sizes[i];
10956 if (!buffer_size) {
10957 /* ERANGE */
10958 path_error(path);
10959 break;
10960 }
10961 buffer = PyMem_MALLOC(buffer_size);
10962 if (!buffer) {
10963 PyErr_NoMemory();
10964 break;
10965 }
10966
10967 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS;
10968 if (path->fd > -1)
10969 length = flistxattr(path->fd, buffer, buffer_size);
10970 else if (follow_symlinks)
10971 length = listxattr(name, buffer, buffer_size);
10972 else
10973 length = llistxattr(name, buffer, buffer_size);
10974 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS;
10975
10976 if (length < 0) {
10977 if (errno == ERANGE) {
10978 PyMem_FREE(buffer);
10979 buffer = NULL;
10980 continue;
10981 }
10982 path_error(path);
10983 break;
10984 }
10985
10986 result = PyList_New(0);
10987 if (!result) {
10988 goto exit;
10989 }
10990
10991 end = buffer + length;
10992 for (trace = start = buffer; trace != end; trace++) {
10993 if (!*trace) {
10994 int error;
10995 PyObject *attribute = PyUnicode_DecodeFSDefaultAndSize(start,
10996 trace - start);
10997 if (!attribute) {
10998 Py_DECREF(result);
10999 result = NULL;
11000 goto exit;
11001 }
11002 error = PyList_Append(result, attribute);
11003 Py_DECREF(attribute);
11004 if (error) {
11005 Py_DECREF(result);
11006 result = NULL;
11007 goto exit;
11008 }
11009 start = trace + 1;
11010 }
11011 }
11012 break;
11013 }
11014exit:
11015 if (buffer)
11016 PyMem_FREE(buffer);
11017 return result;
11018}

11052
11053/* Terminal size querying */
11054
11055static PyTypeObject TerminalSizeType;
11056
11057PyDoc_STRVAR(TerminalSize_docstring,
11058 "A tuple of (columns, lines) for holding terminal window size");
11059
11060static PyStructSequence_Field TerminalSize_fields[] = {
11061 {"columns", "width of the terminal window in characters"},
11062 {"lines", "height of the terminal window in characters"},
11063 {NULL, NULL}
11064};
11065
11066static PyStructSequence_Desc TerminalSize_desc = {
11067 "os.terminal_size",
11068 TerminalSize_docstring,
11069 TerminalSize_fields,
11070 2,
11071};
11072
11073#if defined(TERMSIZE_USE_CONIO) || defined(TERMSIZE_USE_IOCTL)
11074/* AC 3.5: fd should accept None */
11075PyDoc_STRVAR(termsize__doc__,
11076 "Return the size of the terminal window as (columns, lines).\n" \
11077 "\n" \
11078 "The optional argument fd (default standard output) specifies\n" \
11079 "which file descriptor should be queried.\n" \
11080 "\n" \
11081 "If the file descriptor is not connected to a terminal, an OSError\n" \
11082 "is thrown.\n" \
11083 "\n" \
11084 "This function will only be defined if an implementation is\n" \
11085 "available for this system.\n" \
11086 "\n" \
11087 "shutil.get_terminal_size is the high-level function which should \n" \
11088 "normally be used, os.get_terminal_size is the low-level implementation.");
11089
11090static PyObject*
11091get_terminal_size(PyObject *self, PyObject *args)
11092{
11093 int columns, lines;
11094 PyObject *termsize;
11095
11096 int fd = fileno(stdout);
11097 /* Under some conditions stdout may not be connected and
11098 * fileno(stdout) may point to an invalid file descriptor. For example
11099 * GUI apps don't have valid standard streams by default.
11100 *
11101 * If this happens, and the optional fd argument is not present,
11102 * the ioctl below will fail returning EBADF. This is what we want.
11103 */
11104
11105 if (!PyArg_ParseTuple(args, "|i", &fd))
11106 return NULL;
11107
11108#ifdef TERMSIZE_USE_IOCTL
11109 {
11110 struct winsize w;
11111 if (ioctl(fd, TIOCGWINSZ, &w))
11112 return PyErr_SetFromErrno(PyExc_OSError);
11113 columns = w.ws_col;
11114 lines = w.ws_row;
11115 }
11116#endif /* TERMSIZE_USE_IOCTL */
11117
11118#ifdef TERMSIZE_USE_CONIO
11119 {
11120 DWORD nhandle;
11121 HANDLE handle;
11122 CONSOLE_SCREEN_BUFFER_INFO csbi;
11123 switch (fd) {
11124 case 0: nhandle = STD_INPUT_HANDLE;
11125 break;
11126 case 1: nhandle = STD_OUTPUT_HANDLE;
11127 break;
11128 case 2: nhandle = STD_ERROR_HANDLE;
11129 break;
11130 default:
11131 return PyErr_Format(PyExc_ValueError, "bad file descriptor");
11132 }
11133 handle = GetStdHandle(nhandle);
11134 if (handle == NULL)
11135 return PyErr_Format(PyExc_OSError, "handle cannot be retrieved");
11136 if (handle == INVALID_HANDLE_VALUE)
11137 return PyErr_SetFromWindowsErr(0);
11138
11139 if (!GetConsoleScreenBufferInfo(handle, &csbi))
11140 return PyErr_SetFromWindowsErr(0);
11141
11142 columns = csbi.srWindow.Right - csbi.srWindow.Left + 1;
11143 lines = csbi.srWindow.Bottom - csbi.srWindow.Top + 1;
11144 }
11145#endif /* TERMSIZE_USE_CONIO */
11146
11147 termsize = PyStructSequence_New(&TerminalSizeType);
11148 if (termsize == NULL)
11149 return NULL;
11150 PyStructSequence_SET_ITEM(termsize, 0, PyLong_FromLong(columns));
11151 PyStructSequence_SET_ITEM(termsize, 1, PyLong_FromLong(lines));
11152 if (PyErr_Occurred()) {
11153 Py_DECREF(termsize);
11154 return NULL;
11155 }
11156 return termsize;
11157}
11158#endif /* defined(TERMSIZE_USE_CONIO) || defined(TERMSIZE_USE_IOCTL) */
11159
11160
11161/*[clinic input]
11162os.cpu_count
11163
11164Return the number of CPUs in the system; return None if indeterminable.
11165
11166This number is not equivalent to the number of CPUs the current process can
11167use. The number of usable CPUs can be obtained with
11168``len(os.sched_getaffinity(0))``
11169[clinic start generated code]*/
11170
11171static PyObject *
11172os_cpu_count_impl(PyObject *module)
11173/*[clinic end generated code: output=5fc29463c3936a9c input=e7c8f4ba6dbbadd3]*/
11174{
11175 int ncpu = 0;
11176#ifdef MS_WINDOWS
11177 SYSTEM_INFO sysinfo;
11178 GetSystemInfo(&sysinfo);
11179 ncpu = sysinfo.dwNumberOfProcessors;
11180#elif defined(__hpux)
11181 ncpu = mpctl(MPC_GETNUMSPUS, NULL, NULL);
11182#elif defined(HAVE_SYSCONF) && defined(_SC_NPROCESSORS_ONLN)
11183 ncpu = sysconf(_SC_NPROCESSORS_ONLN);
11184#elif defined(__DragonFly__) || \
11185 defined(__OpenBSD__) || \
11186 defined(__FreeBSD__) || \
11187 defined(__NetBSD__) || \
11188 defined(__APPLE__)
11189 int mib[2];
11190 size_t len = sizeof(ncpu);
11191 mib[0] = CTL_HW;
11192 mib[1] = HW_NCPU;
11193 if (sysctl(mib, 2, &ncpu, &len, NULL, 0) != 0)
11194 ncpu = 0;
11195#endif
11196 if (ncpu >= 1)
11197 return PyLong_FromLong(ncpu);
11198 else
11199 Py_RETURN_NONE;
11200}

11295#ifndef MS_WINDOWS
11296PyDoc_STRVAR(get_blocking__doc__,
11297 "get_blocking(fd) -> bool\n" \
11298 "\n" \
11299 "Get the blocking mode of the file descriptor:\n" \
11300 "False if the O_NONBLOCK flag is set, True if the flag is cleared.");
11301
11302static PyObject*
11303posix_get_blocking(PyObject *self, PyObject *args)
11304{
11305 int fd;
11306 int blocking;
11307
11308 if (!PyArg_ParseTuple(args, "i:get_blocking", &fd))
11309 return NULL;
11310
11311 _Py_BEGIN_SUPPRESS_IPH
11312 blocking = _Py_get_blocking(fd);
11313 _Py_END_SUPPRESS_IPH
11314 if (blocking < 0)
11315 return NULL;
11316 return PyBool_FromLong(blocking);
11317}
11318
11319PyDoc_STRVAR(set_blocking__doc__,
11320 "set_blocking(fd, blocking)\n" \
11321 "\n" \
11322 "Set the blocking mode of the specified file descriptor.\n" \
11323 "Set the O_NONBLOCK flag if blocking is False,\n" \
11324 "clear the O_NONBLOCK flag otherwise.");
11325
11326static PyObject*
11327posix_set_blocking(PyObject *self, PyObject *args)
11328{
11329 int fd, blocking, result;
11330
11331 if (!PyArg_ParseTuple(args, "ii:set_blocking", &fd, &blocking))
11332 return NULL;
11333
11334 _Py_BEGIN_SUPPRESS_IPH
11335 result = _Py_set_blocking(fd, blocking);
11336 _Py_END_SUPPRESS_IPH
11337 if (result < 0)
11338 return NULL;
11339 Py_RETURN_NONE;
11340}
11341#endif /* !MS_WINDOWS */

11406static PyObject *
11407DirEntry_fetch_stat(DirEntry *self, int follow_symlinks)
11408{
11409 int result;
11410 STRUCT_STAT st;
11411 PyObject *ub;
11412
11413#ifdef MS_WINDOWS
11414 if (!PyUnicode_FSDecoder(self->path, &ub))
11415 return NULL;
11416 const wchar_t *path = PyUnicode_AsUnicode(ub);
11417#else /* POSIX */
11418 if (!PyUnicode_FSConverter(self->path, &ub))
11419 return NULL;
11420 const char *path = PyBytes_AS_STRING(ub);
11421 if (self->dir_fd != DEFAULT_DIR_FD) {
11422#ifdef HAVE_FSTATAT
11423 result = fstatat(self->dir_fd, path, &st,
11424 follow_symlinks ? 0 : AT_SYMLINK_NOFOLLOW);
11425#else
11426 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_NotImplementedError, "can't fetch stat");
11427 return NULL;
11428#endif /* HAVE_FSTATAT */
11429 }
11430 else
11431#endif
11432 {
11433 if (follow_symlinks)
11434 result = STAT(path, &st);
11435 else
11436 result = LSTAT(path, &st);
11437 }
11438 Py_DECREF(ub);
11439
11440 if (result != 0)
11441 return path_object_error(self->path);
11442
11443 return _pystat_fromstructstat(&st);
11444}

11447DirEntry_get_lstat(DirEntry *self)
11448{
11449 if (!self->lstat) {
11450#ifdef MS_WINDOWS
11451 self->lstat = _pystat_fromstructstat(&self->win32_lstat);
11452#else /* POSIX */
11453 self->lstat = DirEntry_fetch_stat(self, 0);
11454#endif
11455 }
11456 Py_XINCREF(self->lstat);
11457 return self->lstat;
11458}

11460/*[clinic input]
11461os.DirEntry.stat
11462 *
11463 follow_symlinks: bool = True
11464
11465Return stat_result object for the entry; cached per entry.
11466[clinic start generated code]*/
11467
11468static PyObject *
11469os_DirEntry_stat_impl(DirEntry *self, int follow_symlinks)
11470/*[clinic end generated code: output=008593b3a6d01305 input=280d14c1d6f1d00d]*/
11471{
11472 if (!follow_symlinks)
11473 return DirEntry_get_lstat(self);
11474
11475 if (!self->stat) {
11476 int result = os_DirEntry_is_symlink_impl(self);
11477 if (result == -1)
11478 return NULL;
11479 else if (result)
11480 self->stat = DirEntry_fetch_stat(self, 1);
11481 else
11482 self->stat = DirEntry_get_lstat(self);
11483 }
11484
11485 Py_XINCREF(self->stat);
11486 return self->stat;
11487}
11488
11489/* Set exception and return -1 on error, 0 for False, 1 for True */
11490static int
11491DirEntry_test_mode(DirEntry *self, int follow_symlinks, unsigned short mode_bits)
11492{
11493 PyObject *stat = NULL;
11494 PyObject *st_mode = NULL;
11495 long mode;
11496 int result;
11497#if defined(MS_WINDOWS) || defined(HAVE_DIRENT_D_TYPE)
11498 int is_symlink;
11499 int need_stat;
11500#endif
11501#ifdef MS_WINDOWS
11502 unsigned long dir_bits;
11503#endif
11504 _Py_IDENTIFIER(st_mode);
11505
11506#ifdef MS_WINDOWS
11507 is_symlink = (self->win32_lstat.st_mode & S_IFMT) == S_IFLNK;
11508 need_stat = follow_symlinks && is_symlink;
11509#elif defined(HAVE_DIRENT_D_TYPE)
11510 is_symlink = self->d_type == DT_LNK;
11511 need_stat = self->d_type == DT_UNKNOWN || (follow_symlinks && is_symlink);
11512#endif
11513
11514#if defined(MS_WINDOWS) || defined(HAVE_DIRENT_D_TYPE)
11515 if (need_stat) {
11516#endif
11517 stat = os_DirEntry_stat_impl(self, follow_symlinks);
11518 if (!stat) {
11519 if (PyErr_ExceptionMatches(PyExc_FileNotFoundError)) {
11520 /* If file doesn't exist (anymore), then return False
11521 (i.e., say it's not a file/directory) */
11522 PyErr_Clear();
11523 return 0;
11524 }
11525 goto error;
11526 }
11527 st_mode = _PyObject_GetAttrId(stat, &PyId_st_mode);
11528 if (!st_mode)
11529 goto error;
11530
11531 mode = PyLong_AsLong(st_mode);
11532 if (mode == -1 && PyErr_Occurred())
11533 goto error;
11534 Py_CLEAR(st_mode);
11535 Py_CLEAR(stat);
11536 result = (mode & S_IFMT) == mode_bits;
11537#if defined(MS_WINDOWS) || defined(HAVE_DIRENT_D_TYPE)
11538 }
11539 else if (is_symlink) {
11540 assert(mode_bits != S_IFLNK);
11541 result = 0;
11542 }
11543 else {
11544 assert(mode_bits == S_IFDIR || mode_bits == S_IFREG);
11545#ifdef MS_WINDOWS
11546 dir_bits = self->win32_lstat.st_file_attributes & FILE_ATTRIBUTE_DIRECTORY;
11547 if (mode_bits == S_IFDIR)
11548 result = dir_bits != 0;
11549 else
11550 result = dir_bits == 0;
11551#else /* POSIX */
11552 if (mode_bits == S_IFDIR)
11553 result = self->d_type == DT_DIR;
11554 else
11555 result = self->d_type == DT_REG;
11556#endif
11557 }
11558#endif
11559
11560 return result;
11561
11562error:
11563 Py_XDECREF(st_mode);
11564 Py_XDECREF(stat);
11565 return -1;
11566}

11709
11710static wchar_t *
11711join_path_filenameW(const wchar_t *path_wide, const wchar_t *filename)
11712{
11713 Py_ssize_t path_len;
11714 Py_ssize_t size;
11715 wchar_t *result;
11716 wchar_t ch;
11717
11718 if (!path_wide) { /* Default arg: "." */
11719 path_wide = L".";
11720 path_len = 1;
11721 }
11722 else {
11723 path_len = wcslen(path_wide);
11724 }
11725
11726 /* The +1's are for the path separator and the NUL */
11727 size = path_len + 1 + wcslen(filename) + 1;
11728 result = PyMem_New(wchar_t, size);
11729 if (!result) {
11730 PyErr_NoMemory();
11731 return NULL;
11732 }
11733 wcscpy(result, path_wide);
11734 if (path_len > 0) {
11735 ch = result[path_len - 1];
11736 if (ch != SEP && ch != ALTSEP && ch != L':')
11737 result[path_len++] = SEP;
11738 wcscpy(result + path_len, filename);
11739 }
11740 return result;
11741}
11742
11743static PyObject *
11744DirEntry_from_find_data(path_t *path, WIN32_FIND_DATAW *dataW)
11745{
11746 DirEntry *entry;
11747 BY_HANDLE_FILE_INFORMATION file_info;
11748 ULONG reparse_tag;
11749 wchar_t *joined_path;
11750
11751 entry = PyObject_New(DirEntry, &DirEntryType);
11752 if (!entry)
11753 return NULL;
11754 entry->name = NULL;
11755 entry->path = NULL;
11756 entry->stat = NULL;
11757 entry->lstat = NULL;
11758 entry->got_file_index = 0;
11759
11760 entry->name = PyUnicode_FromWideChar(dataW->cFileName, -1);
11761 if (!entry->name)
11762 goto error;
11763 if (path->narrow) {
11764 Py_SETREF(entry->name, PyUnicode_EncodeFSDefault(entry->name));
11765 if (!entry->name)
11766 goto error;
11767 }
11768
11769 joined_path = join_path_filenameW(path->wide, dataW->cFileName);
11770 if (!joined_path)
11771 goto error;
11772
11773 entry->path = PyUnicode_FromWideChar(joined_path, -1);
11774 PyMem_Free(joined_path);
11775 if (!entry->path)
11776 goto error;
11777 if (path->narrow) {
11778 Py_SETREF(entry->path, PyUnicode_EncodeFSDefault(entry->path));
11779 if (!entry->path)
11780 goto error;
11781 }
11782
11783 find_data_to_file_info(dataW, &file_info, &reparse_tag);
11784 _Py_attribute_data_to_stat(&file_info, reparse_tag, &entry->win32_lstat);
11785
11786 return (PyObject *)entry;
11787
11788error:
11789 Py_DECREF(entry);
11790 return NULL;
11791}

11793#else /* POSIX */
11794
11795static char *
11796join_path_filename(const char *path_narrow, const char* filename, Py_ssize_t filename_len)
11797{
11798 Py_ssize_t path_len;
11799 Py_ssize_t size;
11800 char *result;
11801
11802 if (!path_narrow) { /* Default arg: "." */
11803 path_narrow = ".";
11804 path_len = 1;
11805 }
11806 else {
11807 path_len = strlen(path_narrow);
11808 }
11809
11810 if (filename_len == -1)
11811 filename_len = strlen(filename);
11812
11813 /* The +1's are for the path separator and the NUL */
11814 size = path_len + 1 + filename_len + 1;
11815 result = PyMem_New(char, size);
11816 if (!result) {
11817 PyErr_NoMemory();
11818 return NULL;
11819 }
11820 strcpy(result, path_narrow);
11821 if (path_len > 0 && result[path_len - 1] != '/')
11822 result[path_len++] = '/';
11823 strcpy(result + path_len, filename);
11824 return result;
11825}

11827static PyObject *
11828DirEntry_from_posix_info(path_t *path, const char *name, Py_ssize_t name_len,
11829 ino_t d_ino
11830#ifdef HAVE_DIRENT_D_TYPE
11831 , unsigned char d_type
11832#endif
11833 )
11834{
11835 DirEntry *entry;
11836 char *joined_path;
11837
11838 entry = PyObject_New(DirEntry, &DirEntryType);
11839 if (!entry)
11840 return NULL;
11841 entry->name = NULL;
11842 entry->path = NULL;
11843 entry->stat = NULL;
11844 entry->lstat = NULL;
11845
11846 if (path->fd != -1) {
11847 entry->dir_fd = path->fd;
11848 joined_path = NULL;
11849 }
11850 else {
11851 entry->dir_fd = DEFAULT_DIR_FD;
11852 joined_path = join_path_filename(path->narrow, name, name_len);
11853 if (!joined_path)
11854 goto error;
11855 }
11856
11857 if (!path->narrow || !PyObject_CheckBuffer(path->object)) {
11858 entry->name = PyUnicode_DecodeFSDefaultAndSize(name, name_len);
11859 if (joined_path)
11860 entry->path = PyUnicode_DecodeFSDefault(joined_path);
11861 }
11862 else {
11863 entry->name = PyBytes_FromStringAndSize(name, name_len);
11864 if (joined_path)
11865 entry->path = PyBytes_FromString(joined_path);
11866 }
11867 PyMem_Free(joined_path);
11868 if (!entry->name)
11869 goto error;
11870
11871 if (path->fd != -1) {
11872 entry->path = entry->name;
11873 Py_INCREF(entry->path);
11874 }
11875 else if (!entry->path)
11876 goto error;
11877
11878#ifdef HAVE_DIRENT_D_TYPE
11879 entry->d_type = d_type;
11880#endif
11881 entry->d_ino = d_ino;
11882
11883 return (PyObject *)entry;
11884
11885error:
11886 Py_XDECREF(entry);
11887 return NULL;
11888}
11889
11890#endif

11892
11893typedef struct {
11894 PyObject_HEAD
11895 path_t path;
11896#ifdef MS_WINDOWS
11897 HANDLE handle;
11898 WIN32_FIND_DATAW file_data;
11899 int first_time;
11900#else /* POSIX */
11901 DIR *dirp;
11902#endif
11903#ifdef HAVE_FDOPENDIR
11904 int fd;
11905#endif
11906} ScandirIterator;
11907
11908#ifdef MS_WINDOWS
11909
11910static int
11911ScandirIterator_is_closed(ScandirIterator *iterator)
11912{
11913 return iterator->handle == INVALID_HANDLE_VALUE;
11914}
11915
11916static void
11917ScandirIterator_closedir(ScandirIterator *iterator)
11918{
11919 HANDLE handle = iterator->handle;
11920
11921 if (handle == INVALID_HANDLE_VALUE)
11922 return;
11923
11924 iterator->handle = INVALID_HANDLE_VALUE;
11925 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
11926 FindClose(handle);
11927 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
11928}
11929
11930static PyObject *
11931ScandirIterator_iternext(ScandirIterator *iterator)
11932{
11933 WIN32_FIND_DATAW *file_data = &iterator->file_data;
11934 BOOL success;
11935 PyObject *entry;
11936
11937 /* Happens if the iterator is iterated twice, or closed explicitly */
11938 if (iterator->handle == INVALID_HANDLE_VALUE)
11939 return NULL;
11940
11941 while (1) {
11942 if (!iterator->first_time) {
11943 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
11944 success = FindNextFileW(iterator->handle, file_data);
11945 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
11946 if (!success) {
11947 /* Error or no more files */
11948 if (GetLastError() != ERROR_NO_MORE_FILES)
11949 path_error(&iterator->path);
11950 break;
11951 }
11952 }
11953 iterator->first_time = 0;
11954
11955 /* Skip over . and .. */
11956 if (wcscmp(file_data->cFileName, L".") != 0 &&
11957 wcscmp(file_data->cFileName, L"..") != 0) {
11958 entry = DirEntry_from_find_data(&iterator->path, file_data);
11959 if (!entry)
11960 break;
11961 return entry;
11962 }
11963
11964 /* Loop till we get a non-dot directory or finish iterating */
11965 }
11966
11967 /* Error or no more files */
11968 ScandirIterator_closedir(iterator);
11969 return NULL;
11970}
11971
11972#else /* POSIX */
11973
11974static int
11975ScandirIterator_is_closed(ScandirIterator *iterator)
11976{
11977 return !iterator->dirp;
11978}
11979
11980static void
11981ScandirIterator_closedir(ScandirIterator *iterator)
11982{
11983 DIR *dirp = iterator->dirp;
11984
11985 if (!dirp)
11986 return;
11987
11988 iterator->dirp = NULL;
11989 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
11990#ifdef HAVE_FDOPENDIR
11991 if (iterator->path.fd != -1)
11992 rewinddir(dirp);
11993#endif
11994 closedir(dirp);
11995 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
11996 return;
11997}
11998
11999static PyObject *
12000ScandirIterator_iternext(ScandirIterator *iterator)
12001{
12002 struct dirent *direntp;
12003 Py_ssize_t name_len;
12004 int is_dot;
12005 PyObject *entry;
12006
12007 /* Happens if the iterator is iterated twice, or closed explicitly */
12008 if (!iterator->dirp)
12009 return NULL;
12010
12011 while (1) {
12012 errno = 0;
12013 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
12014 direntp = readdir(iterator->dirp);
12015 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
12016
12017 if (!direntp) {
12018 /* Error or no more files */
12019 if (errno != 0)
12020 path_error(&iterator->path);
12021 break;
12022 }
12023
12024 /* Skip over . and .. */
12025 name_len = NAMLEN(direntp);
12026 is_dot = direntp->d_name[0] == '.' &&
12027 (name_len == 1 || (direntp->d_name[1] == '.' && name_len == 2));
12028 if (!is_dot) {
12029 entry = DirEntry_from_posix_info(&iterator->path, direntp->d_name,
12030 name_len, direntp->d_ino
12031#ifdef HAVE_DIRENT_D_TYPE
12032 , direntp->d_type
12033#endif
12034 );
12035 if (!entry)
12036 break;
12037 return entry;
12038 }
12039
12040 /* Loop till we get a non-dot directory or finish iterating */
12041 }
12042
12043 /* Error or no more files */
12044 ScandirIterator_closedir(iterator);
12045 return NULL;
12046}
12047
12048#endif
12049
12050static PyObject *
12051ScandirIterator_close(ScandirIterator *self, PyObject *args)
12052{
12053 ScandirIterator_closedir(self);
12054 Py_RETURN_NONE;
12055}
12056
12057static PyObject *
12058ScandirIterator_enter(PyObject *self, PyObject *args)
12059{
12060 Py_INCREF(self);
12061 return self;
12062}
12063
12064static PyObject *
12065ScandirIterator_exit(ScandirIterator *self, PyObject *args)
12066{
12067 ScandirIterator_closedir(self);
12068 Py_RETURN_NONE;
12069}
12070
12071static void
12072ScandirIterator_finalize(ScandirIterator *iterator)
12073{
12074 PyObject *error_type, *error_value, *error_traceback;
12075
12076 /* Save the current exception, if any. */
12077 PyErr_Fetch(&error_type, &error_value, &error_traceback);
12078
12079 if (!ScandirIterator_is_closed(iterator)) {
12080 ScandirIterator_closedir(iterator);
12081
12082 if (PyErr_ResourceWarning((PyObject *)iterator, 1,
12083 "unclosed scandir iterator %R", iterator)) {
12084 /* Spurious errors can appear at shutdown */
12085 if (PyErr_ExceptionMatches(PyExc_Warning)) {
12086 PyErr_WriteUnraisable((PyObject *) iterator);
12087 }
12088 }
12089 }
12090
12091 path_cleanup(&iterator->path);
12092
12093 /* Restore the saved exception. */
12094 PyErr_Restore(error_type, error_value, error_traceback);
12095}
12096
12097static void
12098ScandirIterator_dealloc(ScandirIterator *iterator)
12099{
12100 if (PyObject_CallFinalizerFromDealloc((PyObject *)iterator) < 0)
12101 return;
12102
12103 Py_TYPE(iterator)->tp_free((PyObject *)iterator);
12104}
12105

12108 {"__exit__", (PyCFunction)ScandirIterator_exit, METH_VARARGS},
12109 {"close", (PyCFunction)ScandirIterator_close, METH_NOARGS},
12110 {NULL}
12111};

12166/*[clinic input]
12167os.scandir
12168
12169 path : path_t(nullable=True, allow_fd='PATH_HAVE_FDOPENDIR') = None
12170
12171Return an iterator of DirEntry objects for given path.
12172
12173path can be specified as either str, bytes or path-like object. If path
12174is bytes, the names of yielded DirEntry objects will also be bytes; in
12175all other circumstances they will be str.
12176
12177If path is None, uses the path='.'.
12178[clinic start generated code]*/
12179
12180static PyObject *
12181os_scandir_impl(PyObject *module, path_t *path)
12182/*[clinic end generated code: output=6eb2668b675ca89e input=b139dc1c57f60846]*/
12183{
12184 ScandirIterator *iterator;
12185#ifdef MS_WINDOWS
12186 wchar_t *path_strW;
12187#else
12188 const char *path_str;
12189#ifdef HAVE_FDOPENDIR
12190 int fd = -1;
12191#endif
12192#endif
12193
12194 iterator = PyObject_New(ScandirIterator, &ScandirIteratorType);
12195 if (!iterator)
12196 return NULL;
12197
12198#ifdef MS_WINDOWS
12199 iterator->handle = INVALID_HANDLE_VALUE;
12200#else
12201 iterator->dirp = NULL;
12202#endif
12203
12204 memcpy(&iterator->path, path, sizeof(path_t));
12205 /* Move the ownership to iterator->path */
12206 path->object = NULL;
12207 path->cleanup = NULL;
12208
12209#ifdef MS_WINDOWS
12210 iterator->first_time = 1;
12211
12212 path_strW = join_path_filenameW(iterator->path.wide, L"*.*");
12213 if (!path_strW)
12214 goto error;
12215
12216 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
12217 iterator->handle = FindFirstFileW(path_strW, &iterator->file_data);
12218 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
12219
12220 PyMem_Free(path_strW);
12221
12222 if (iterator->handle == INVALID_HANDLE_VALUE) {
12223 path_error(&iterator->path);
12224 goto error;
12225 }
12226#else /* POSIX */
12227 errno = 0;
12228#ifdef HAVE_FDOPENDIR
12229 if (path->fd != -1) {
12230 /* closedir() closes the FD, so we duplicate it */
12231 fd = _Py_dup(path->fd);
12232 if (fd == -1)
12233 goto error;
12234
12235 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
12236 iterator->dirp = fdopendir(fd);
12237 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
12238 }
12239 else
12240#endif
12241 {
12242 if (iterator->path.narrow)
12243 path_str = iterator->path.narrow;
12244 else
12245 path_str = ".";
12246
12247 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
12248 iterator->dirp = opendir(path_str);
12249 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
12250 }
12251
12252 if (!iterator->dirp) {
12253 path_error(&iterator->path);
12254#ifdef HAVE_FDOPENDIR
12255 if (fd != -1) {
12256 Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
12257 close(fd);
12258 Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
12259 }
12260#endif
12261 goto error;
12262 }
12263#endif
12264
12265 return (PyObject *)iterator;
12266
12267error:
12268 Py_DECREF(iterator);
12269 return NULL;
12270}

12272/*
12273 Return the file system path representation of the object.
12274
12275 If the object is str or bytes, then allow it to pass through with
12276 an incremented refcount. If the object defines __fspath__(), then
12277 return the result of that method. All other types raise a TypeError.
12278*/
12279PyObject *
12280PyOS_FSPath(PyObject *path)
12281{
12282 /* For error message reasons, this function is manually inlined in
12283 path_converter(). */
12284 _Py_IDENTIFIER(__fspath__);
12285 PyObject *func = NULL;
12286 PyObject *path_repr = NULL;
12287
12288 if (PyUnicode_Check(path) || PyBytes_Check(path)) {
12289 Py_INCREF(path);
12290 return path;
12291 }
12292
12293 func = _PyObject_LookupSpecial(path, &PyId___fspath__);
12294 if (NULL == func) {
12295 return PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
12296 "expected str, bytes or os.PathLike object, "
12297 "not %.200s",
12298 Py_TYPE(path)->tp_name);
12299 }
12300
12301 path_repr = _PyObject_CallNoArg(func);
12302 Py_DECREF(func);
12303 if (NULL == path_repr) {
12304 return NULL;
12305 }
12306
12307 if (!(PyUnicode_Check(path_repr) || PyBytes_Check(path_repr))) {
12308 PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
12309 "expected %.200s.__fspath__() to return str or bytes, "
12310 "not %.200s", Py_TYPE(path)->tp_name,
12311 Py_TYPE(path_repr)->tp_name);
12312 Py_DECREF(path_repr);
12313 return NULL;
12314 }
12315
12316 return path_repr;
12317}
12318
12319/*[clinic input]
12320os.fspath
12321
12322 path: object
12323
12324Return the file system path representation of the object.
12325
12326If the object is str or bytes, then allow it to pass through as-is. If the
12327object defines __fspath__(), then return the result of that method. All other
12328types raise a TypeError.
12329[clinic start generated code]*/
12330
12331static PyObject *
12332os_fspath_impl(PyObject *module, PyObject *path)
12333/*[clinic end generated code: output=c3c3b78ecff2914f input=e357165f7b22490f]*/
12334{
12335 return PyOS_FSPath(path);
12336}

12338#ifdef HAVE_GETRANDOM_SYSCALL
12339/*[clinic input]
12340os.getrandom
12341
12342 size: Py_ssize_t
12343 flags: int=0
12344
12345Obtain a series of random bytes.
12346[clinic start generated code]*/
12347
12348static PyObject *
12349os_getrandom_impl(PyObject *module, Py_ssize_t size, int flags)
12350/*[clinic end generated code: output=b3a618196a61409c input=59bafac39c594947]*/
12351{
12352 PyObject *bytes;
12353 Py_ssize_t n;
12354
12355 if (size < 0) {
12356 errno = EINVAL;
12357 return posix_error();
12358 }
12359
12360 bytes = PyBytes_FromStringAndSize(NULL, size);
12361 if (bytes == NULL) {
12362 PyErr_NoMemory();
12363 return NULL;
12364 }
12365
12366 while (1) {
12367 n = syscall(SYS_getrandom,
12368 PyBytes_AS_STRING(bytes),
12369 PyBytes_GET_SIZE(bytes),
12370 flags);
12371 if (n < 0 && errno == EINTR) {
12372 if (PyErr_CheckSignals() < 0) {
12373 goto error;
12374 }
12375
12376 /* getrandom() was interrupted by a signal: retry */
12377 continue;
12378 }
12379 break;
12380 }
12381
12382 if (n < 0) {
12383 PyErr_SetFromErrno(PyExc_OSError);
12384 goto error;
12385 }
12386
12387 if (n != size) {
12388 _PyBytes_Resize(&bytes, n);
12389 }
12390
12391 return bytes;
12392
12393error:
12394 Py_DECREF(bytes);
12395 return NULL;
12396}
12397#endif /* HAVE_GETRANDOM_SYSCALL */

12596#if defined(HAVE_SYMLINK) && defined(MS_WINDOWS)
12597static int
12598enable_symlink()
12599{
12600 HANDLE tok;
12601 TOKEN_PRIVILEGES tok_priv;
12602 LUID luid;
12603
12604 if (!OpenProcessToken(GetCurrentProcess(), TOKEN_ALL_ACCESS, &tok))
12605 return 0;
12606
12607 if (!LookupPrivilegeValue(NULL, SE_CREATE_SYMBOLIC_LINK_NAME, &luid))
12608 return 0;
12609
12610 tok_priv.PrivilegeCount = 1;
12611 tok_priv.Privileges[0].Luid = luid;
12612 tok_priv.Privileges[0].Attributes = SE_PRIVILEGE_ENABLED;
12613
12614 if (!AdjustTokenPrivileges(tok, FALSE, &tok_priv,
12615 sizeof(TOKEN_PRIVILEGES),
12616 (PTOKEN_PRIVILEGES) NULL, (PDWORD) NULL))
12617 return 0;
12618
12619 /* ERROR_NOT_ALL_ASSIGNED returned when the privilege can't be assigned. */
12620 return GetLastError() == ERROR_NOT_ALL_ASSIGNED ? 0 : 1;
12621}
12622#endif /* defined(HAVE_SYMLINK) && defined(MS_WINDOWS) */

13188
13189PyMODINIT_FUNC
13190INITFUNC(void)
13191{
13192 PyObject *m, *v;
13193 PyObject *list;
13194 const char * const *trace;
13195
13196#if defined(HAVE_SYMLINK) && defined(MS_WINDOWS)
13197 win32_can_symlink = enable_symlink();
13198#endif
13199
13200 m = PyModule_Create(&posixmodule);
13201 if (m == NULL)
13202 return NULL;
13203
13204 /* Initialize environ dictionary */
13205 v = convertenviron();
13206 Py_XINCREF(v);
13207 if (v == NULL || PyModule_AddObject(m, "environ", v) != 0)
13208 return NULL;
13209 Py_DECREF(v);
13210
13211 if (all_ins(m))
13212 return NULL;
13213
13214 if (setup_confname_tables(m))
13215 return NULL;
13216
13217 Py_INCREF(PyExc_OSError);
13218 PyModule_AddObject(m, "error", PyExc_OSError);
13219
13220#ifdef HAVE_PUTENV
13221 if (posix_putenv_garbage == NULL)
13222 posix_putenv_garbage = PyDict_New();
13223#endif
13224
13225 if (!initialized) {
13226#if defined(HAVE_WAITID) && !defined(__APPLE__)
13227 waitid_result_desc.name = MODNAME ".waitid_result";
13228 if (PyStructSequence_InitType2(&WaitidResultType, &waitid_result_desc) < 0)
13229 return NULL;
13230#endif
13231
13232 stat_result_desc.name = "os.stat_result"; /* see issue #19209 */
13233 stat_result_desc.fields[7].name = PyStructSequence_UnnamedField;
13234 stat_result_desc.fields[8].name = PyStructSequence_UnnamedField;
13235 stat_result_desc.fields[9].name = PyStructSequence_UnnamedField;
13236 if (PyStructSequence_InitType2(&StatResultType, &stat_result_desc) < 0)
13237 return NULL;
13238 structseq_new = StatResultType.tp_new;
13239 StatResultType.tp_new = statresult_new;
13240
13241 statvfs_result_desc.name = "os.statvfs_result"; /* see issue #19209 */
13242 if (PyStructSequence_InitType2(&StatVFSResultType,
13243 &statvfs_result_desc) < 0)
13244 return NULL;
13245#ifdef NEED_TICKS_PER_SECOND
13246# if defined(HAVE_SYSCONF) && defined(_SC_CLK_TCK)
13247 ticks_per_second = sysconf(_SC_CLK_TCK);
13248# elif defined(HZ)
13249 ticks_per_second = HZ;
13250# else
13251 ticks_per_second = 60; /* magic fallback value; may be bogus */
13252# endif
13253#endif
13254
13255#if defined(HAVE_SCHED_SETPARAM) || defined(HAVE_SCHED_SETSCHEDULER)
13256 sched_param_desc.name = MODNAME ".sched_param";
13257 if (PyStructSequence_InitType2(&SchedParamType, &sched_param_desc) < 0)
13258 return NULL;
13259 SchedParamType.tp_new = os_sched_param;
13260#endif
13261
13262 /* initialize TerminalSize_info */
13263 if (PyStructSequence_InitType2(&TerminalSizeType,
13264 &TerminalSize_desc) < 0)
13265 return NULL;
13266
13267 /* initialize scandir types */
13268 if (PyType_Ready(&ScandirIteratorType) < 0)
13269 return NULL;
13270 if (PyType_Ready(&DirEntryType) < 0)
13271 return NULL;
13272 }
13273#if defined(HAVE_WAITID) && !defined(__APPLE__)
13274 Py_INCREF((PyObject*) &WaitidResultType);
13275 PyModule_AddObject(m, "waitid_result", (PyObject*) &WaitidResultType);
13276#endif
13277 Py_INCREF((PyObject*) &StatResultType);
13278 PyModule_AddObject(m, "stat_result", (PyObject*) &StatResultType);
13279 Py_INCREF((PyObject*) &StatVFSResultType);
13280 PyModule_AddObject(m, "statvfs_result",
13281 (PyObject*) &StatVFSResultType);
13282
13283#if defined(HAVE_SCHED_SETPARAM) || defined(HAVE_SCHED_SETSCHEDULER)
13284 Py_INCREF(&SchedParamType);
13285 PyModule_AddObject(m, "sched_param", (PyObject *)&SchedParamType);
13286#endif
13287
13288 times_result_desc.name = MODNAME ".times_result";
13289 if (PyStructSequence_InitType2(&TimesResultType, &times_result_desc) < 0)
13290 return NULL;
13291 PyModule_AddObject(m, "times_result", (PyObject *)&TimesResultType);
13292
13293 uname_result_desc.name = MODNAME ".uname_result";
13294 if (PyStructSequence_InitType2(&UnameResultType, &uname_result_desc) < 0)
13295 return NULL;
13296 PyModule_AddObject(m, "uname_result", (PyObject *)&UnameResultType);
13297
13298#ifdef __APPLE__
13299 /*
13300 * Step 2 of weak-linking support on Mac OS X.
13301 *
13302 * The code below removes functions that are not available on the
13303 * currently active platform.
13304 *
13305 * This block allow one to use a python binary that was build on
13306 * OSX 10.4 on OSX 10.3, without losing access to new APIs on
13307 * OSX 10.4.
13308 */
13309#ifdef HAVE_FSTATVFS
13310 if (fstatvfs == NULL) {
13311 if (PyObject_DelAttrString(m, "fstatvfs") == -1) {
13312 return NULL;
13313 }
13314 }
13315#endif /* HAVE_FSTATVFS */
13316
13317#ifdef HAVE_STATVFS
13318 if (statvfs == NULL) {
13319 if (PyObject_DelAttrString(m, "statvfs") == -1) {
13320 return NULL;
13321 }
13322 }
13323#endif /* HAVE_STATVFS */
13324
13325# ifdef HAVE_LCHOWN
13326 if (lchown == NULL) {
13327 if (PyObject_DelAttrString(m, "lchown") == -1) {
13328 return NULL;
13329 }
13330 }
13331#endif /* HAVE_LCHOWN */
13332
13333
13334#endif /* __APPLE__ */
13335
13336 Py_INCREF(&TerminalSizeType);
13337 PyModule_AddObject(m, "terminal_size", (PyObject*) &TerminalSizeType);
13338
13339 billion = PyLong_FromLong(1000000000);
13340 if (!billion)
13341 return NULL;
13342
13343 /* suppress "function not used" warnings */
13344 {
13345 int ignored;
13346 fd_specified("", -1);
13347 follow_symlinks_specified("", 1);
13348 dir_fd_and_follow_symlinks_invalid("chmod", DEFAULT_DIR_FD, 1);
13349 dir_fd_converter(Py_None, &ignored);
13350 dir_fd_unavailable(Py_None, &ignored);
13351 }
13352
13353 /*
13354 * provide list of locally available functions
13355 * so os.py can populate support_* lists
13356 */
13357 list = PyList_New(0);
13358 if (!list)
13359 return NULL;
13360 for (trace = have_functions; *trace; trace++) {
13361 PyObject *unicode = PyUnicode_DecodeASCII(*trace, strlen(*trace), NULL);
13362 if (!unicode)
13363 return NULL;
13364 if (PyList_Append(list, unicode))
13365 return NULL;
13366 Py_DECREF(unicode);
13367 }
13368 PyModule_AddObject(m, "_have_functions", list);
13369
13370 Py_INCREF((PyObject *) &DirEntryType);
13371 PyModule_AddObject(m, "DirEntry", (PyObject *)&DirEntryType);
13372
13373 initialized = 1;
13374
13375 return m;
13376}

13379}
